1
00:00:01,180 --> 00:00:02,919
Listen to me carefully.

2
00:00:02,920 --> 00:00:04,579
Which is better? Being maliciously edited...

3
00:00:04,580 --> 00:00:06,889
- or being entirely edited out? - Okay.

4
00:00:06,890 --> 00:00:08,789
- I asked Yeong Cheol this question. - I see.

5
00:00:08,790 --> 00:00:10,919
He said being maliciously edited would be better.

6
00:00:10,920 --> 00:00:12,259
- What? - Evil editing is better.

7
00:00:12,260 --> 00:00:14,359
- I'd rather be entirely edited out. - Really? Why?

8
00:00:14,360 --> 00:00:15,829
- That's what I'm talking about. - Yes. Here's why.

9
00:00:15,830 --> 00:00:17,129
If I can't leave a good impression,

10
00:00:17,130 --> 00:00:18,670
I'd rather just start from scratch.

11
00:00:18,800 --> 00:00:20,999
- I don't really know... Wait. What? - Right. That makes sense.

12
00:00:21,000 --> 00:00:22,099
- Listen, guys. Whatever happens, - What?

13
00:00:22,100 --> 00:00:23,300
it's better than getting sent off.

14
00:00:24,840 --> 00:00:26,569
(The soccer legends are here.)

15
00:00:26,570 --> 00:00:28,270
- Oh, my. - What a great hook for the opening!

16
00:00:28,410 --> 00:00:29,540
(Cheering)

17
00:00:29,680 --> 00:00:32,179
- He's right about that. - Korea!

18
00:00:32,180 --> 00:00:33,380
(The soccer fans' hearts begin to pound.)

19
00:00:33,680 --> 00:00:35,350
Don't bring up the topic about getting sent off.

20
00:00:36,250 --> 00:00:37,319
- Is that what you prefer? - Yes.

21
00:00:37,320 --> 00:00:38,919
- Hi. We're from... - Where did you transfer from?

22
00:00:38,920 --> 00:00:42,319
We Made Korean Soccer History High School.

23
00:00:42,320 --> 00:00:43,860
I kept a clean sheet throughout the World Soccer Games.

24
00:00:44,360 --> 00:00:46,229
- I'm Kim Young Kwang. - We all know that.

25
00:00:46,230 --> 00:00:48,089
- You didn't concede a single goal? - That's right.

26
00:00:48,090 --> 00:00:49,499
- He kept a clean sheet? Awesome. - Yes.

27
00:00:49,500 --> 00:00:51,630
I'm the fighter on the pitch, Kim Tae Young.

28
00:00:52,730 --> 00:00:54,629
- He's known as Tiger Mask. - Tiger Mask!

29
00:00:54,630 --> 00:00:56,739
- I'm the Master of the Left Foot, - Exactly.

30
00:00:56,740 --> 00:00:57,740
Ha Seok Ju.

31
00:00:58,610 --> 00:01:00,039
- Oh, hold on. - The Master of the Left Foot.

32
00:01:00,040 --> 00:01:01,169
- Shall we chant? It's been a while. - Okay.

33
00:01:01,170 --> 00:01:02,980
Korea!

34
00:01:04,210 --> 00:01:06,049
The World Soccer Games is less than a month away.

35
00:01:06,050 --> 00:01:08,719
- That's right. - Actually, one of us is...

36
00:01:08,720 --> 00:01:10,879
- an uncertified soccer player. - That's right.

37
00:01:10,880 --> 00:01:13,389
You know, soccer players have their own unique way of greeting.

38
00:01:13,390 --> 00:01:15,020
- Yes, that's right. - They have their own way?

39
00:01:15,160 --> 00:01:17,859
- How do they greet each other? - When we meet in the morning...

40
00:01:17,860 --> 00:01:19,929
Just as basketball players pass the ball to each other,

41
00:01:19,930 --> 00:01:22,029
- soccer players use their feet. - They use their feet?

42
00:01:22,030 --> 00:01:23,230
By the way, this soccer ball is...

43
00:01:23,460 --> 00:01:25,869
the official match ball for the 2026 World Soccer Games.

44
00:01:25,870 --> 00:01:26,969
- Really? - Really?

45
00:01:26,970 --> 00:01:28,099
Yes, this is the official match ball.

46
00:01:28,100 --> 00:01:29,100
(Trionda Pro, symbolizing the unity of the 3 host countries)

47
00:01:29,101 --> 00:01:30,969
Show us how you dribble...

48
00:01:30,970 --> 00:01:32,669
- before showing us how you greet. - I told you before.

49
00:01:32,670 --> 00:01:34,439
- Young Kwang can save any shot. - I was a goalkeeper.

50
00:01:34,440 --> 00:01:35,539
- I'm sure you can flick the ball. - Show us your hand skills.

51
00:01:35,540 --> 00:01:36,609
Can you kick the ball toward me?

52
00:01:36,610 --> 00:01:37,639
Kick the ball.

53
00:01:37,640 --> 00:01:39,380
- You can kick it hard. - Really?

54
00:01:41,210 --> 00:01:42,220
Really?

55
00:01:42,550 --> 00:01:44,479
(He catches it easily.)

56
00:01:44,480 --> 00:01:46,149
- Did you see how he caught it? - He's like Spider Man.

57
00:01:46,150 --> 00:01:47,190
- Kick it. - You can kick it.

58
00:01:48,790 --> 00:01:50,889
- What just happened? - Kick it this time.

59
00:01:50,890 --> 00:01:52,959
- I can't kick it accurately. - Kick it this time.

60
00:01:52,960 --> 00:01:54,889
It should be the master that kicks it.

61
00:01:54,890 --> 00:01:55,899
- Oh, my. - For real?

62
00:01:55,900 --> 00:01:56,900
(Catching the ball)

63
00:01:56,930 --> 00:01:57,930
Right now...

64
00:01:58,700 --> 00:02:01,029
(Young Kwang saves even the shot of the Master of the Left Foot.)

65
00:02:01,030 --> 00:02:02,499
- That was amazing. - That was so fascinating.

66
00:02:02,500 --> 00:02:03,969
- Should I kick it hard? - Yes, kick it hard this time.

67
00:02:03,970 --> 00:02:05,639
- It gets sucked into his hands. - Kick it a little bit harder.

68
00:02:05,640 --> 00:02:06,909
- A little bit harder. - Harder than that?

69
00:02:06,910 --> 00:02:07,910
- Just a little bit harder. - Kick it harder.

70
00:02:09,710 --> 00:02:11,080
- Hold on a second. - Amazing.

71
00:02:11,680 --> 00:02:13,579
(He suddenly dives.)

72
00:02:13,580 --> 00:02:15,549
- Hold on a second. - Diving wasn't necessary.

73
00:02:15,550 --> 00:02:16,679
- Young Kwang, why did you lie down? - That wasn't necessary.

74
00:02:16,680 --> 00:02:18,149
- Diving wasn't necessary. - Why did you lie down?

75
00:02:18,150 --> 00:02:19,449
- Young Kwang, why did you dive? - It was necessary.

76
00:02:19,450 --> 00:02:21,389
- A goalie needs to put on a show. - What was that?

77
00:02:21,390 --> 00:02:23,119
- He put on a show. - Soo Geun, catch the ball.

78
00:02:23,120 --> 00:02:24,619
- That was a great show. - Soo Geun, catch the ball.

79
00:02:24,620 --> 00:02:25,629
- Really? - Yes.

80
00:02:25,630 --> 00:02:27,060
- That's too weak. - Soo Geun is good at it too.

81
00:02:27,360 --> 00:02:28,660
- That's what I'm talking about. - He put on a show.

82
00:02:28,830 --> 00:02:30,260
- He put on a show. - That was good.

83
00:02:30,360 --> 00:02:31,700
- That's too weak. - Soo Geun is good at it too.

84
00:02:31,930 --> 00:02:33,999
(Holding the ball in his arms,)

85
00:02:34,000 --> 00:02:35,100
(he falls down.)

86
00:02:35,470 --> 00:02:36,539
(The perfect comedian's version of a performance)

87
00:02:36,540 --> 00:02:38,299
- Shin Young, catch it. - That was good.

88
00:02:38,300 --> 00:02:39,670
- That's good. - Catch it.

89
00:02:40,340 --> 00:02:42,439
(Rolling on the floor)

90
00:02:42,440 --> 00:02:43,739
- That was... - That's good.

91
00:02:43,740 --> 00:02:44,740
(The ball bounces off her chest.)

92
00:02:44,741 --> 00:02:46,910
(After making a secure catch,)

93
00:02:48,010 --> 00:02:50,080
(she suddenly throws herself to protect the official match ball.)

94
00:02:50,580 --> 00:02:52,789
- Shin Young, that was... - Doesn't it hurt?

95
00:02:52,790 --> 00:02:53,790
Hold on.

96
00:02:54,020 --> 00:02:57,289
- You looked like mini Lee Woon Jae. - Sometimes...

97
00:02:57,290 --> 00:02:58,290
- Lee Woon Jae? - Yes.

98
00:02:58,291 --> 00:02:59,660
(When it's time to put on a show, her hands are impenetrable.)

99
00:02:59,860 --> 00:03:01,789
- Let's see their juggling skills. - Let's see their juggling skills.

100
00:03:01,790 --> 00:03:03,329
- They can juggle all day long... - Juggling.

101
00:03:03,330 --> 00:03:04,999
- as long as they get fed. - One, two, three, four...

102
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:06,330
- Really? - Yes.

103
00:03:06,670 --> 00:03:07,670
See? He's keeping the ball off the floor.

104
00:03:07,671 --> 00:03:09,440
- He can do this all day long? - That's amazing.

105
00:03:09,640 --> 00:03:12,240
(The juggling performance)

106
00:03:12,410 --> 00:03:14,609
Young Kwang, do goalkeepers practice juggling too?

107
00:03:14,610 --> 00:03:15,610
- Of course. - All players do that, right?

108
00:03:15,611 --> 00:03:17,179
- I'm good at juggling with my head. - Hold on a second.

109
00:03:17,180 --> 00:03:18,880
- One, two, three, four... - He'll start.

110
00:03:19,310 --> 00:03:20,950
- And six... Oh, my. - He's really good at it.

111
00:03:21,680 --> 00:03:22,850
Indeed. Oh, my goodness.

112
00:03:23,120 --> 00:03:24,279
- Stall the ball. - Amazing.

113
00:03:24,280 --> 00:03:25,850
(He lets it land on his forehead and shows off his head stall skill.)

114
00:03:26,490 --> 00:03:27,490
He does know how to juggle.

115
00:03:28,450 --> 00:03:30,219
- He has amazing skills. - I'm amazed.

116
00:03:30,220 --> 00:03:31,389
Juggling skills don't necessarily make you a great soccer player.

117
00:03:31,390 --> 00:03:32,529
- That's true. - Exactly.

118
00:03:32,530 --> 00:03:34,059
- That's true. - He's right about that.

119
00:03:34,060 --> 00:03:35,859
- I'm really bad at juggling. - Right.

120
00:03:35,860 --> 00:03:37,259
- Honestly, I'm bad at it. - I see.

121
00:03:37,260 --> 00:03:38,770
But I was a great soccer player.

122
00:03:39,600 --> 00:03:41,399
Don't let the ball fall on the floor.

123
00:03:41,400 --> 00:03:42,799
- Ready. - Come closer to one another.

124
00:03:42,800 --> 00:03:43,969
I shouldn't be doing this with them.

125
00:03:43,970 --> 00:03:45,640
Okay. Two.

126
00:03:45,970 --> 00:03:47,609
- Pass it on the second touch. - That's right.

127
00:03:47,610 --> 00:03:49,439
If he says 2, you should pass it on your 2nd touch.

128
00:03:49,440 --> 00:03:51,109
- That didn't even count. - I guess it's their own rule,

129
00:03:51,110 --> 00:03:52,749
juggling the ball the number of times the other person calls out.

130
00:03:52,750 --> 00:03:54,049
- If I say two... - Got it.

131
00:03:54,050 --> 00:03:55,650
You should pass the ball on your second touch like this.

132
00:03:56,150 --> 00:03:57,150
Five.

133
00:03:57,151 --> 00:03:58,349
- Let's limit the number to three. - "Five?"

134
00:03:58,350 --> 00:03:59,649
(The difficulty level soared.)

135
00:03:59,650 --> 00:04:00,889
- What? - He called out five.

136
00:04:00,890 --> 00:04:02,060
- Let's limit the number to three. - "Five?"

137
00:04:03,360 --> 00:04:04,459
- Three. - Three.

138
00:04:04,460 --> 00:04:05,959
- Three. - Three.

139
00:04:05,960 --> 00:04:07,490
- Two. - Ten.

140
00:04:08,290 --> 00:04:09,429
You can't call out ten.

141
00:04:09,430 --> 00:04:11,659
- Two, three, four, five, - Four, five,

142
00:04:11,660 --> 00:04:13,299
- six, seven, eight, - six, seven, eight...

143
00:04:13,300 --> 00:04:14,429
- nine, ten. - Twenty.

144
00:04:14,430 --> 00:04:16,239
Twenty?

145
00:04:16,240 --> 00:04:18,599
Hey! What are you doing?

146
00:04:18,600 --> 00:04:20,109
- Calm down. - That was...

147
00:04:20,110 --> 00:04:21,839
(He tries to punish Young Kwang for doubling the number.)

148
00:04:21,840 --> 00:04:23,180
- Just like that... - Red card!

149
00:04:23,310 --> 00:04:25,549
- He called out twenty. My gosh. - Red card.

150
00:04:25,550 --> 00:04:26,979
Young Kwang wins!

151
00:04:26,980 --> 00:04:28,310
- Yes! - Young Kwang wins!

152
00:04:29,180 --> 00:04:30,849
- That seemed so much fun. - I guess soccer players...

153
00:04:30,850 --> 00:04:32,119
- can have fun together... - They're so incredible.

154
00:04:32,120 --> 00:04:34,019
- when they have a ball. - Exactly.

155
00:04:34,020 --> 00:04:35,920
- Did you guys know? - That was awesome.

156
00:04:36,420 --> 00:04:37,560
One of them...

157
00:04:37,960 --> 00:04:40,359
transferred to our school through his connection with Jang Hoon.

158
00:04:40,360 --> 00:04:41,789
- I know that. - Is it Seok Ju?

159
00:04:41,790 --> 00:04:44,160
- That's not true. I didn't... - Who is it?

160
00:04:44,630 --> 00:04:45,729
- I didn't help anyone get cast... - Is it Tae Young?

161
00:04:45,730 --> 00:04:46,730
It's...

162
00:04:48,570 --> 00:04:50,599
- Young Kwang. - That's not true.

163
00:04:50,600 --> 00:04:51,839
He's the first member to join Jang Hoon's clan.

164
00:04:51,840 --> 00:04:52,969
There's no such thing as "Jang Hoon's clan."

165
00:04:52,970 --> 00:04:55,609
- There was no one in his clan. - You're the king of variety shows.

166
00:04:55,610 --> 00:04:57,040
- I'm the first member. - That's right.

167
00:04:57,180 --> 00:04:59,210
(When Young Kwang appeared on "Yes Man...")

168
00:04:59,450 --> 00:05:00,679
(As the 1st member of Jang Hoon's clan...)

169
00:05:00,680 --> 00:05:02,650
(Excuse me?)

170
00:05:03,020 --> 00:05:05,020
(Even Jang Hoon seems to have no idea.)

171
00:05:05,280 --> 00:05:07,320
(Are you ditching soccer for basketball now?)

172
00:05:07,490 --> 00:05:08,619
- What happened? - Why "Jang Hoon's clan?"

173
00:05:08,620 --> 00:05:10,259
I've never heard "Jang Hoon's clan."

174
00:05:10,260 --> 00:05:11,559
- And he's the first member? - That's right.

175
00:05:11,560 --> 00:05:12,729
Young Kwang, is that true?

176
00:05:12,730 --> 00:05:14,959
Yes, that's true. I was going to join Ho Dong's clan.

177
00:05:14,960 --> 00:05:16,200
But it was hard to join his.

178
00:05:16,500 --> 00:05:17,729
- Oh, Ho Dong's clan? - I see.

179
00:05:17,730 --> 00:05:18,869
- But... - It's hard to join his clan.

180
00:05:18,870 --> 00:05:20,030
Ho Dong hasn't looked out for his men in a long time.

181
00:05:21,570 --> 00:05:23,770
- He hasn't been so helpful, has he? - He doesn't take care of them.

182
00:05:24,170 --> 00:05:25,369
- He hasn't been helpful. - Right.

183
00:05:25,370 --> 00:05:26,439
- He... - There's no one in my clan.

184
00:05:26,440 --> 00:05:28,040
- dismantled his own line. - That's right.

185
00:05:28,270 --> 00:05:30,309
I'm the only one barely hanging onto that line.

186
00:05:30,310 --> 00:05:31,310
Like this?

187
00:05:31,310 --> 00:05:32,310
- Yes. - That's so funny.

188
00:05:32,850 --> 00:05:34,350
He let go of everyone else below me.

189
00:05:34,650 --> 00:05:35,919
- Oh, I didn't know that. - That's why they all come here...

190
00:05:35,920 --> 00:05:37,779
- and complain about it. - Right.

191
00:05:37,780 --> 00:05:40,420
(The history of Ho Dong's clan was revealed through their disclosures.)

192
00:05:40,620 --> 00:05:42,559
- After that... - Did he play off your energy well?

193
00:05:42,560 --> 00:05:44,159
- He played off my energy very well. - I did at first,

194
00:05:44,160 --> 00:05:45,629
- but as time went by, - Come on.

195
00:05:45,630 --> 00:05:47,560
- I got tired. - He laughed genuinely.

196
00:05:48,090 --> 00:05:49,329
He laughed genuinely?

197
00:05:49,330 --> 00:05:51,029
- He's similar to me. - I saw it.

198
00:05:51,030 --> 00:05:52,629
- He laughed genuinely? - I can tell his fake laughter...

199
00:05:52,630 --> 00:05:53,969
- from his genuine laughter. - Right.

200
00:05:53,970 --> 00:05:55,969
- He laughed his head off. - You just laughed genuinely, right?

201
00:05:55,970 --> 00:05:57,339
- He laughed out loud. - Really?

202
00:05:57,340 --> 00:05:59,169
- So, he really laughed genuinely. - Look at him.

203
00:05:59,170 --> 00:06:00,569
- He's smiling from ear to ear. - He's funny.

204
00:06:00,570 --> 00:06:03,740
- He's funny, indeed. - As you keep watching him,

205
00:06:03,910 --> 00:06:05,340
you'll find him funny at first,

206
00:06:05,850 --> 00:06:07,150
but you'll get tired of him eventually.

207
00:06:07,550 --> 00:06:08,550
But...

208
00:06:08,551 --> 00:06:10,319
- But... - Young Kwang,

209
00:06:10,320 --> 00:06:12,449
is it true that one of us makes you uncomfortable?

210
00:06:12,450 --> 00:06:14,249
- Is there anyone who does that? - To be honest,

211
00:06:14,250 --> 00:06:15,459
- I feel so uncomfortable here. - They're all his seniors.

212
00:06:15,460 --> 00:06:16,820
- Why? - Here's why.

213
00:06:17,020 --> 00:06:18,390
Seok Ju is 16 years older than me.

214
00:06:18,760 --> 00:06:21,289
- He's 16 years older than you? - And he's 13 years older than me.

215
00:06:21,290 --> 00:06:23,929
In soccer, if you're 12 years older,

216
00:06:23,930 --> 00:06:25,500
- you're called "uncle." - Oh, goodness.

217
00:06:25,730 --> 00:06:27,299
When I joined my first pro team,

218
00:06:27,300 --> 00:06:28,430
Tae Young was the oldest player there.

219
00:06:28,670 --> 00:06:29,899
I used to call him "uncle," so speaking casually to him...

220
00:06:29,900 --> 00:06:31,099
- is very uncomfortable. - You used to call him "uncle."

221
00:06:31,100 --> 00:06:33,209
- Jeonnam Dragons. - We played for Jeonnam Dragons.

222
00:06:33,210 --> 00:06:34,470
- He was your senior player. - Yes.

223
00:06:34,570 --> 00:06:36,839
Even a one-year age gap...

224
00:06:36,840 --> 00:06:38,309
- Even a one-year age gap? - That's a huge gap.

225
00:06:38,310 --> 00:06:39,479
- Exactly. - The three of you...

226
00:06:39,480 --> 00:06:42,180
- Were the three of you close? - Actually...

227
00:06:42,220 --> 00:06:44,819
I've never played soccer with Young Kwang before.

228
00:06:44,820 --> 00:06:45,989
- We met on "Shooting Stars." - Right.

229
00:06:45,990 --> 00:06:47,050
Tae Young is like my minion.

230
00:06:47,450 --> 00:06:48,989
- "Minion?" - Are you guys close now?

231
00:06:48,990 --> 00:06:51,420
- It's true. - I haven't heard it in a long time.

232
00:06:51,920 --> 00:06:53,789
- He's my minion. - You must have many minions.

233
00:06:53,790 --> 00:06:56,159
They would do anything I tell them to.

234
00:06:56,160 --> 00:06:57,799
They used to fold my laundry and everything.

235
00:06:57,800 --> 00:06:59,469
- They used to do such things? - I see.

236
00:06:59,470 --> 00:07:00,470
- Tae Young seems... - They set the table for me...

237
00:07:00,470 --> 00:07:01,470
- to have a lot to say. - before we ate.

238
00:07:01,471 --> 00:07:03,739
- I'll tell you a story. - Okay.

239
00:07:03,740 --> 00:07:05,940
He made me do his laundry, but those were not his socks.

240
00:07:06,240 --> 00:07:08,469
Since there were many players, we wrote down numbers...

241
00:07:08,470 --> 00:07:09,579
- on our socks. - Oh, I see.

242
00:07:09,580 --> 00:07:11,710
He took someone else's socks that were new.

243
00:07:13,780 --> 00:07:14,879
- Did I do that? - Yes, you did.

244
00:07:14,880 --> 00:07:16,520
(Seok Ju pretends he knows nothing about it.)

245
00:07:17,020 --> 00:07:18,020
Let's talk after the shoot.

246
00:07:18,050 --> 00:07:19,120
"Let's talk after the shoot."

247
00:07:21,290 --> 00:07:23,959
- Everyone speaks casually here. - By the way...

248
00:07:23,960 --> 00:07:27,559
We always remembered Tae Young...

249
00:07:27,560 --> 00:07:29,829
as the reliable veteran...

250
00:07:29,830 --> 00:07:31,059
- and big-brother figure of... - That's right.

251
00:07:31,060 --> 00:07:33,600
- the 2002 World Soccer Games team. - The oldest brother.

252
00:07:33,800 --> 00:07:35,869
- But since he's with Seok Ju here, - Absolutely.

253
00:07:35,870 --> 00:07:37,799
- he looks like... - He's the second oldest one.

254
00:07:37,800 --> 00:07:39,909
a man who's tiptoeing around his older brother.

255
00:07:39,910 --> 00:07:41,069
That's right.

256
00:07:41,070 --> 00:07:43,039
- When I arrived here, - Seok Ju, do you have a complaint?

257
00:07:43,040 --> 00:07:44,210
I honestly thought...

258
00:07:44,510 --> 00:07:48,480
that you should've invited Coaches Park Hang Seo or Cha Bum Kun.

259
00:07:49,620 --> 00:07:51,249
- I, too, have a lot to say. - We invited them,

260
00:07:51,250 --> 00:07:52,920
but they refused to come because you would be here.

261
00:07:53,790 --> 00:07:55,989
- We asked them to be here. - Yes, we did.

262
00:07:55,990 --> 00:07:58,489
- We called them. - Right.

263
00:07:58,490 --> 00:07:59,490
They refused to come.

264
00:07:59,760 --> 00:08:01,189
He's so charming.

265
00:08:01,190 --> 00:08:03,100
- Right. He's charming, indeed. - Yes.

266
00:08:03,500 --> 00:08:05,629
- He's hilarious. - Seok Ju, if you were here...

267
00:08:05,630 --> 00:08:07,600
with Coaches Park Hang Seo and Cha Bum Kun,

268
00:08:07,770 --> 00:08:08,869
how would you speak casually to them?

269
00:08:08,870 --> 00:08:09,969
- Right. - "Bum Kun, have you been well?"

270
00:08:09,970 --> 00:08:11,100
- "Bum Kun." - I would say like this.

271
00:08:11,200 --> 00:08:12,510
- He said it so comfortably. - Right.

272
00:08:13,170 --> 00:08:14,909
- "Hey, Hang Seo." - "Hey, Hang Seo?"

273
00:08:14,910 --> 00:08:17,140
"What have you been up to in Vietnam?"

274
00:08:17,680 --> 00:08:19,909
- It sounds a bit awkward. - Right.

275
00:08:19,910 --> 00:08:22,219
I'm sorry to say this. Even though we know one another,

276
00:08:22,220 --> 00:08:24,619
and you're soccer legends who represented Korea,

277
00:08:24,620 --> 00:08:26,390
you have to go through transfer process.

278
00:08:26,620 --> 00:08:28,119
- Or else, you can't enroll here. - Right.

279
00:08:28,120 --> 00:08:30,059
- Please bring me what you prepared. - Right.

280
00:08:30,060 --> 00:08:31,460
- Go on. You just have to submit it. - All right.

281
00:08:32,230 --> 00:08:34,259
Soo Geun, here's our transfer form.

282
00:08:34,260 --> 00:08:35,599
- What is he doing? - He put it on his head.

283
00:08:35,600 --> 00:08:37,029
- Take it on your head. - On my head?

284
00:08:37,030 --> 00:08:38,300
- Receive it. - Oh, he headed it...

285
00:08:39,400 --> 00:08:40,499
(As a soccer legend, he delivered the document by heading it.)

286
00:08:40,500 --> 00:08:42,699
He had to do something funny as the second oldest guest.

287
00:08:42,700 --> 00:08:43,939
- He has a good sense of humor. - He was better at heading...

288
00:08:43,940 --> 00:08:45,169
than kicking.

289
00:08:45,170 --> 00:08:47,269
- Right, absolutely. - He was better at it than kicking?

290
00:08:47,270 --> 00:08:48,769
He blocked a lot of shots with headers.

291
00:08:48,770 --> 00:08:49,879
- Yes, he was the best. - I hurt my forehead.

292
00:08:49,880 --> 00:08:51,439
He would get a cut on his forehead.

293
00:08:51,440 --> 00:08:53,149
- I'd get a cut or a bruise. - That's right.

294
00:08:53,150 --> 00:08:55,409
You can sit on the chairs now. Sit comfortably.

295
00:08:55,410 --> 00:08:56,880
Good timing. I'm so tired.

296
00:08:58,220 --> 00:09:00,489
- He was most excited to sit down. - We should take good care of him.

297
00:09:00,490 --> 00:09:01,490
Or else, he'll keep grumbling.

298
00:09:01,491 --> 00:09:02,759
- Really? - We should take good care of him.

299
00:09:02,760 --> 00:09:04,190
Does he grumble or whine?

300
00:09:05,660 --> 00:09:07,060
(I'll see you guys after the shoot.)

301
00:09:07,860 --> 00:09:10,200
The transfer form to Men on a Mission. Names.

302
00:09:10,300 --> 00:09:12,370
Ha Seok Ju, Kim Tae Young, and Kim Young Kwang.

303
00:09:13,270 --> 00:09:14,399
Great.

304
00:09:14,400 --> 00:09:18,000
First, they wrote down their nicknames.

305
00:09:18,370 --> 00:09:20,309
I think this nickname is related to soccer.

306
00:09:20,310 --> 00:09:21,839
Seok Ju's nickname is...

307
00:09:21,840 --> 00:09:23,440
- Master of the Left Foot. - Master of the Left Foot.

308
00:09:24,080 --> 00:09:25,380
- Master of the Left Foot. - Master of the Left Foot.

309
00:09:25,480 --> 00:09:27,009
- Actually, young people... - He was amazing.

310
00:09:27,010 --> 00:09:28,580
these days...

311
00:09:28,750 --> 00:09:30,619
might only recognize him from his role as the chairman...

312
00:09:30,620 --> 00:09:32,119
- on "Shooting Stars." - Right.

313
00:09:32,120 --> 00:09:33,449
But when we were younger,

314
00:09:33,450 --> 00:09:34,719
he was known...

315
00:09:34,720 --> 00:09:35,990
- as the Master of the Left Foot. - Absolutely.

316
00:09:36,260 --> 00:09:40,089
- In every international match, - Right.

317
00:09:40,090 --> 00:09:42,760
he played as a midfielder.

318
00:09:43,260 --> 00:09:45,899
He played really well. He was an incredible soccer player.

319
00:09:45,900 --> 00:09:47,599
- He was amazing. - I heard stories of some athletes.

320
00:09:47,600 --> 00:09:49,299
For example, a right-handed tennis player...

321
00:09:49,300 --> 00:09:50,940
switched to playing lefty...

322
00:09:51,240 --> 00:09:52,670
- to gain a competitive advantage. - Right.

323
00:09:52,840 --> 00:09:54,410
- That wouldn't work in soccer. - Are you naturally left-footed?

324
00:09:54,740 --> 00:09:56,110
I'm left-handed and left-footed.

325
00:09:56,710 --> 00:09:58,680
- Oh, I see. - You're a natural lefty?

326
00:09:58,840 --> 00:10:00,249
It's like his right leg belongs to someone else.

327
00:10:00,250 --> 00:10:01,250
My right leg...

328
00:10:01,510 --> 00:10:03,350
Why would you say such a thing?

329
00:10:03,650 --> 00:10:06,090
- Today's episode is so funny. - He has no control over that leg?

330
00:10:06,190 --> 00:10:07,590
It's as if it were someone else's leg.

331
00:10:07,950 --> 00:10:10,189
- So it's basically a borrowed leg? - Yes, exactly.

332
00:10:10,190 --> 00:10:11,590
Just as Young Kwang said,

333
00:10:12,090 --> 00:10:14,090
my right leg is basically someone else's.

334
00:10:14,760 --> 00:10:16,359
- So Young Kwang was right about it. - His right leg...

335
00:10:16,360 --> 00:10:17,600
I told you, it's basically someone else's leg.

336
00:10:17,700 --> 00:10:20,500
I use my left foot 99.9 percent of the time.

337
00:10:20,900 --> 00:10:22,840
Seok Ju, you wore a soccer shoe only on your left foot, right?

338
00:10:23,200 --> 00:10:24,339
(Blinking)

339
00:10:24,340 --> 00:10:25,739
- Are you okay? - And a slipper on his right foot.

340
00:10:25,740 --> 00:10:26,769
Right.

341
00:10:26,770 --> 00:10:27,909
Did you wear a sneaker on your right foot?

342
00:10:27,910 --> 00:10:29,139
He wore a slipper on his right foot.

343
00:10:29,140 --> 00:10:31,379
- He only wore a sock on that foot. - He must regret being here.

344
00:10:31,380 --> 00:10:33,709
- He wore a shoe only on one foot. - His facial expressions are funny.

345
00:10:33,710 --> 00:10:34,750
(Put a shoe on Seok Ju's right foot.)

346
00:10:35,180 --> 00:10:36,549
You wore a soccer shoe only on one foot?

347
00:10:36,550 --> 00:10:38,949
- I can feel him fuming right now. - Right.

348
00:10:38,950 --> 00:10:39,989
(I can feel him fuming right now.)

349
00:10:39,990 --> 00:10:41,549
- Only on your left foot... - I'm calm and happy now.

350
00:10:41,550 --> 00:10:43,189
- Are you? - Yes, I'm enjoying myself.

351
00:10:43,190 --> 00:10:44,319
Did you wear a sneaker...

352
00:10:44,320 --> 00:10:45,489
- on your right foot? - Exactly.

353
00:10:45,490 --> 00:10:47,030
Would you wear a soccer shoe only on one foot?

354
00:10:47,960 --> 00:10:49,099
He's upset.

355
00:10:49,100 --> 00:10:50,300
- He's upset. - He's upset.

356
00:10:50,930 --> 00:10:52,100
But here's the thing.

357
00:10:52,230 --> 00:10:53,429
My left shoe wore out...

358
00:10:53,430 --> 00:10:54,630
- way faster than the right one. - Right.

359
00:10:55,030 --> 00:10:56,639
- My right shoe barely wore out. - You mainly used your left foot.

360
00:10:56,640 --> 00:10:59,509
- So I kept the right shoe... - I see.

361
00:10:59,510 --> 00:11:00,870
and only fixed the left one.

362
00:11:01,640 --> 00:11:03,509
In modern soccer,

363
00:11:03,510 --> 00:11:05,410
- there are many two-footed players. - Two-footed players. Right.

364
00:11:05,710 --> 00:11:07,979
Many players train to become two-footed.

365
00:11:07,980 --> 00:11:09,009
In modern soccer,

366
00:11:09,010 --> 00:11:10,249
- two-footed players... - That's right.

367
00:11:10,250 --> 00:11:11,749
- become internationally renowned. - Right.

368
00:11:11,750 --> 00:11:12,819
Such players include Son Heung Min.

369
00:11:12,820 --> 00:11:14,549
- Lee Kang In also uses both feet... - That's right.

370
00:11:14,550 --> 00:11:16,619
- although he's left-footed. - He tries to be two-footed.

371
00:11:16,620 --> 00:11:19,429
So, Seok Ju was famous as the Master of the Left Foot,

372
00:11:19,430 --> 00:11:21,030
but it wouldn't cut it in modern soccer.

373
00:11:21,190 --> 00:11:22,290
- Yes, that's right. - That's right.

374
00:11:23,260 --> 00:11:24,500
It was an advantage only back in the day.

375
00:11:25,660 --> 00:11:28,770
- Being two-footed is today's trend. - Seok Ju seems angry.

376
00:11:29,470 --> 00:11:30,700
I don't know what you guys are talking about.

377
00:11:31,240 --> 00:11:32,840
- You don't have to know. - He's angry.

378
00:11:32,940 --> 00:11:35,240
- You don't have to know. - If you look back at the old days,

379
00:11:36,040 --> 00:11:38,440
Seok Ju was good at passing...

380
00:11:38,880 --> 00:11:40,750
- and scored a lot of goals. - He scored a lot of goals.

381
00:11:40,850 --> 00:11:42,949
- He mainly used his left foot, - Exactly.

382
00:11:42,950 --> 00:11:44,379
- but he was a great player. - He was the best.

383
00:11:44,380 --> 00:11:46,690
- I didn't need to be two-footed. - That's right.

384
00:11:46,920 --> 00:11:48,649
He was a national team player even though he only used one foot.

385
00:11:48,650 --> 00:11:50,189
- Right. - Imagine him being two-footed.

386
00:11:50,190 --> 00:11:51,759
- He would've shaken the world. - Indeed.

387
00:11:51,760 --> 00:11:52,929
Seok Ju refrained from being too good.

388
00:11:52,930 --> 00:11:55,489
They wouldn't be able to beat me even if they were two-footed.

389
00:11:55,490 --> 00:11:58,000
(Talking big)

390
00:11:58,200 --> 00:12:00,200
Hearing him say it, it actually sounds right.

391
00:12:00,500 --> 00:12:02,700
- It's just right. I never lie. - Let's move on.

392
00:12:02,970 --> 00:12:05,200
- Tae Young's nickname has changed. - What?

393
00:12:05,300 --> 00:12:07,609
- It's General Kim. - General Kim?

394
00:12:07,610 --> 00:12:10,780
Coach Lee Hoe Taek gave me that nickname.

395
00:12:11,010 --> 00:12:14,650
It means I lead the charge and fight on the field like a general.

396
00:12:15,310 --> 00:12:16,920
He always calls me like this. "Hey, General Kim."

397
00:12:17,650 --> 00:12:19,049
He intimidated other players with his charisma.

398
00:12:19,050 --> 00:12:21,289
- He used to be called Tiger Mask. - Tiger Mask.

399
00:12:21,290 --> 00:12:22,820
- Taegeuk Mask. - Taegeuk Mask.

400
00:12:22,990 --> 00:12:24,359
- He was so cool back then. - "Taegeuk Mask?"

401
00:12:24,360 --> 00:12:26,729
- I mean, Tiger Mask. - He was mostly known as Tiger Mask.

402
00:12:26,730 --> 00:12:28,629
- That's right. - I wore a mask...

403
00:12:28,630 --> 00:12:31,200
- during the World Soccer Games. - Right.

404
00:12:31,700 --> 00:12:34,500
Young Kwang has such a long nickname.

405
00:12:35,000 --> 00:12:37,699
- One is No Pain Kim Young Kwang. - Yes.

406
00:12:37,700 --> 00:12:39,939
- No Pain Kim Young Kwang. - The other is Top Dog of Suncheon.

407
00:12:39,940 --> 00:12:41,439
(Nickname: No Pain Kim Young Kwang, Top Dog of Suncheon)

408
00:12:41,440 --> 00:12:43,579
It sounds like an ID for Buddy Buddy.

409
00:12:43,580 --> 00:12:45,309
- What kind of nickname is that? - Top Dog of Suncheon?

410
00:12:45,310 --> 00:12:46,380
Top Dog of Suncheon?

411
00:12:46,610 --> 00:12:47,810
- That's so tacky. - Hey.

412
00:12:48,310 --> 00:12:51,420
- You're too old to be called that. - I didn't come up with that.

413
00:12:51,720 --> 00:12:54,120
- Young Kwang is the same age as me. - Many of my friends in Suncheon...

414
00:12:54,520 --> 00:12:55,859
gave me that nickname.

415
00:12:55,860 --> 00:12:58,119
- Were you the top dog of Suncheon? - He's the top dog of Masan.

416
00:12:58,120 --> 00:12:59,560
(The two top dogs of the Yeongnam and Honam regions meet.)

417
00:12:59,830 --> 00:13:01,830
- You see, I really feel no pain. - Kim Young Kwang...

418
00:13:02,060 --> 00:13:03,460
- Really? - A short-form clip of me...

419
00:13:04,030 --> 00:13:07,000
that proves I don't feel pain got more than 20 million views.

420
00:13:07,630 --> 00:13:09,539
It became the talk of the town.

421
00:13:09,540 --> 00:13:11,069
Jung Chan Sung hit me twice...

422
00:13:11,070 --> 00:13:12,610
- with his low kicks. - I saw that clip.

423
00:13:12,910 --> 00:13:13,910
(Groaning)

424
00:13:14,410 --> 00:13:16,439
(Korean Zombie's low kicks made the legendary athlete kneel.)

425
00:13:16,440 --> 00:13:17,480
(Groaning)

426
00:13:18,210 --> 00:13:19,210
(Kicking)

427
00:13:19,210 --> 00:13:20,210
(No reaction)

428
00:13:21,110 --> 00:13:23,020
(He seems calm and peaceful.)

429
00:13:23,180 --> 00:13:24,579
- I was okay. - Didn't you get bruises?

430
00:13:24,580 --> 00:13:26,190
- No. I ran around the next day. - You know...

431
00:13:26,320 --> 00:13:29,220
Young Kwang, goalkeepers...

432
00:13:29,490 --> 00:13:31,419
get hit in the face when the ball moves...

433
00:13:31,420 --> 00:13:32,689
faster than their hands can react.

434
00:13:32,690 --> 00:13:35,029
- Right. - Many of them faint.

435
00:13:35,030 --> 00:13:36,660
- That's true. - You must not faint.

436
00:13:36,830 --> 00:13:38,630
- Oh, gosh. - I enjoyed that.

437
00:13:39,130 --> 00:13:40,699
- It happens sometimes. - He enjoyed that.

438
00:13:40,700 --> 00:13:43,399
- He's insane. - He really is Top Dog of Suncheon.

439
00:13:43,400 --> 00:13:45,500
- Sometimes... - While sliding,

440
00:13:45,840 --> 00:13:47,339
- they hit their heads... - Yes.

441
00:13:47,340 --> 00:13:49,379
- against the goalpost. - I got 100 stitches in my face.

442
00:13:49,380 --> 00:13:50,439
- Are you saying 100 stitches? - Really?

443
00:13:50,440 --> 00:13:51,580
- I got 100 stitches in my face. - In your face?

444
00:13:51,640 --> 00:13:53,879
Let's say someone rips a shot right in front of me.

445
00:13:53,880 --> 00:13:55,950
On camera, it looks like I made the save.

446
00:13:56,120 --> 00:13:58,220
But actually, the ball bounced off my face.

447
00:13:58,850 --> 00:14:00,650
I wouldn't want to let anyone know it bounced off my face.

448
00:14:00,720 --> 00:14:01,890
So I would get up instantly...

449
00:14:02,390 --> 00:14:03,520
and pretend I'm okay.

450
00:14:03,690 --> 00:14:04,989
- That's a little bit... - You'd be caught on camera.

451
00:14:04,990 --> 00:14:07,790
- I'd look like this in slow motion. - Exactly.

452
00:14:08,690 --> 00:14:11,599
So you just try to keep looking cool and strong.

453
00:14:11,600 --> 00:14:13,129
- Yes, exactly. - You put on a performance.

454
00:14:13,130 --> 00:14:15,030
- Yes. I must never look weak. - You put on a performance.

455
00:14:15,230 --> 00:14:17,099
What were your positions?

456
00:14:17,100 --> 00:14:18,839
- Young Kwang was... - I was a goalkeeper.

457
00:14:18,840 --> 00:14:20,709
- GK. - And Tae Young was...

458
00:14:20,710 --> 00:14:23,380
- I covered the entire backline. - You were a defender.

459
00:14:23,540 --> 00:14:25,280
- What about you, Seok Ju? - I was an all-rounder.

460
00:14:25,380 --> 00:14:26,449
- He was a utility player. - Oh, my.

461
00:14:26,450 --> 00:14:27,879
- What? How... - He could play any position.

462
00:14:27,880 --> 00:14:28,979
Are there all-rounders in soccer?

463
00:14:28,980 --> 00:14:31,149
- He was mainly a midfielder. - Right.

464
00:14:31,150 --> 00:14:32,380
- A wing midfielder? - I covered every position.

465
00:14:32,590 --> 00:14:34,219
- I'm curious about something. - As a midfielder...

466
00:14:34,220 --> 00:14:36,719
In the case of judo,

467
00:14:36,720 --> 00:14:37,859
coaches assign roles...

468
00:14:37,860 --> 00:14:39,930
- based on players' physical builds. - Yes.

469
00:14:40,290 --> 00:14:42,799
Do soccer coaches assign positions?

470
00:14:42,800 --> 00:14:44,660
- Or do players choose their roles? - Oh, I didn't think of that.

471
00:14:44,830 --> 00:14:47,230
I used to play as a striker because I liked it.

472
00:14:47,700 --> 00:14:48,800
But I didn't perform well.

473
00:14:48,900 --> 00:14:50,100
(Oh, boy)

474
00:14:50,340 --> 00:14:52,440
I've tried every position, including striker, midfielder,

475
00:14:52,870 --> 00:14:54,910
fullback, wingback, and center-back.

476
00:14:55,070 --> 00:14:56,380
- I played as a defender too. - He played every position.

477
00:14:56,480 --> 00:14:59,210
Except for goalkeeper. I was sent behind the goal.

478
00:14:59,580 --> 00:15:01,509
- As a ball boy. - You became a ball boy.

479
00:15:01,510 --> 00:15:04,250
One day, both of the two goalkeepers got injured.

480
00:15:04,520 --> 00:15:05,720
The coach asked if anyone wanted to play goalkeeper.

481
00:15:05,820 --> 00:15:07,650
I volunteered. That's how I started playing goalkeeper.

482
00:15:08,050 --> 00:15:09,220
Did you block all the shots that day?

483
00:15:09,360 --> 00:15:11,920
I made it to the national team in just five months.

484
00:15:12,890 --> 00:15:14,059
- In 5 months. - In 5 months?

485
00:15:14,060 --> 00:15:16,030
I made the elementary school national youth team.

486
00:15:16,560 --> 00:15:18,599
The injuries of those goalkeepers changed his life.

487
00:15:18,600 --> 00:15:19,669
- That's right. - Exactly.

488
00:15:19,670 --> 00:15:21,069
- That's absolutely true. - Had you become a field player...

489
00:15:21,070 --> 00:15:22,500
What would you be doing now?

490
00:15:23,170 --> 00:15:24,539
- How hilarious. - "What would you be doing now?"

491
00:15:24,540 --> 00:15:26,210
I would've focused on being Top Dog of Suncheon.

492
00:15:26,310 --> 00:15:27,910
- "What would you be doing now?" - He wouldn't be here.

493
00:15:28,070 --> 00:15:29,209
- "What would you be doing now?" - He would've...

494
00:15:29,210 --> 00:15:31,039
He would've focused on being Top Dog of Suncheon.

495
00:15:31,040 --> 00:15:33,509
- He'd be Top Dog of Suncheon. - Back then... That's right.

496
00:15:33,510 --> 00:15:35,209
- That was a blessing. I'm grateful. - "There's a guy in Suncheon..."

497
00:15:35,210 --> 00:15:36,879
"who doesn't feel pain."

498
00:15:36,880 --> 00:15:37,880
(The 1st member of Jang Hoon's clan makes Jang Hoon laugh genuinely.)

499
00:15:37,881 --> 00:15:41,019
What about you, Seok Ju? Did you choose to be a midfielder?

500
00:15:41,020 --> 00:15:42,350
- The coach told me where to be. - He's a utility player.

501
00:15:43,220 --> 00:15:45,619
I played different positions, but I couldn't complain.

502
00:15:45,620 --> 00:15:48,290
- Right. The coach knew... - The coach had an eye for talent.

503
00:15:48,490 --> 00:15:49,759
I switched positions based on the coach's instructions.

504
00:15:49,760 --> 00:15:51,560
When it didn't work well for the team,

505
00:15:51,660 --> 00:15:53,200
I switched positions again.

506
00:15:53,500 --> 00:15:56,099
- But... - Smart ones can adjust to it.

507
00:15:56,100 --> 00:15:57,870
- They adapt to any position? - Yes.

508
00:15:58,040 --> 00:15:59,369
- Smart ones can do that. - That's true.

509
00:15:59,370 --> 00:16:01,609
- You need to be smart in soccer. - That's right.

510
00:16:01,610 --> 00:16:02,779
- Right. You need to be smart... - Those who were called...

511
00:16:02,780 --> 00:16:03,940
top dogs like Young Kwang...

512
00:16:04,240 --> 00:16:05,880
- are usually not very smart. - That's funny.

513
00:16:06,150 --> 00:16:08,950
"Those who were called top dogs..."

514
00:16:09,110 --> 00:16:11,619
Tae Young, were you always a defender?

515
00:16:11,620 --> 00:16:14,250
No. When I was little, I was a winger.

516
00:16:14,490 --> 00:16:16,960
- Because I was quite fast. - He's fast, indeed.

517
00:16:17,090 --> 00:16:20,190
When I started high school, I had to switch positions.

518
00:16:20,290 --> 00:16:21,590
- Because he didn't have techniques. - A defender...

519
00:16:23,230 --> 00:16:25,859
- He didn't have techniques? - That makes sense.

520
00:16:25,860 --> 00:16:26,929
(Tae Young had no techniques, and Young Kwang wasn't smart.)

521
00:16:26,930 --> 00:16:29,300
- He's completely spot on with that. - He had no techniques?

522
00:16:30,240 --> 00:16:31,339
Did you just use your intelligence?

523
00:16:31,340 --> 00:16:33,140
- So I... - He just smashed it.

524
00:16:33,310 --> 00:16:36,939
So I became a defender, and my coach said I was a reliable defender.

525
00:16:36,940 --> 00:16:39,449
I played defender throughout my soccer career.

526
00:16:39,450 --> 00:16:41,279
- Because he had no techniques. - I kept playing defender.

527
00:16:41,280 --> 00:16:43,419
I heard that Coach Hiddink said,

528
00:16:43,420 --> 00:16:45,549
- "Tae Young..." - He's hilarious.

529
00:16:45,550 --> 00:16:46,849
- "is a good player..." - He must have some techniques.

530
00:16:46,850 --> 00:16:48,889
- I bet he has some kind of license. - Right.

531
00:16:48,890 --> 00:16:50,519
- He must have some kind of license. - Stop it already.

532
00:16:50,520 --> 00:16:52,560
- By the way, Tae Young is... - He must have some kind of license.

533
00:16:52,930 --> 00:16:55,959
- a bit short for a center-back. - He's a bit short.

534
00:16:55,960 --> 00:16:57,600
- I'm 180cm tall, so I was short. - Right?

535
00:16:57,800 --> 00:16:59,629
Despite his height,

536
00:16:59,630 --> 00:17:01,470
- he played center-back... - He ran until the last minute.

537
00:17:01,700 --> 00:17:03,040
- during the World Soccer Games. - Exactly.

538
00:17:04,440 --> 00:17:07,910
In high school and college, I did a lot of jump training using stairs.

539
00:17:09,310 --> 00:17:11,609
While ordinary people jump three steps at a time,

540
00:17:11,610 --> 00:17:14,310
- I could leap up 5 or 6 steps. - Really?

541
00:17:14,650 --> 00:17:16,950
Even though I was only 180cm tall, I could hang in the air for long...

542
00:17:17,220 --> 00:17:18,319
- during aerial battles. - Oh, he...

543
00:17:18,320 --> 00:17:20,850
- He has a jumping technique. - Right. He has a technique.

544
00:17:21,120 --> 00:17:23,190
- Right. - You call jumping a technique?

545
00:17:24,160 --> 00:17:26,790
- Jumping rope improves your jump. - That's right.

546
00:17:27,090 --> 00:17:28,189
You just have to jump rope a lot.

547
00:17:28,190 --> 00:17:29,799
- So, he just has great stamina? - Oh, that's right.

548
00:17:29,800 --> 00:17:31,129
You can improve your vertical jump through effort.

549
00:17:31,130 --> 00:17:32,199
Oh, I see.

550
00:17:32,200 --> 00:17:34,429
- It's not a natural talent? - It's the result of effort.

551
00:17:34,430 --> 00:17:36,940
Looking back at the time...

552
00:17:37,040 --> 00:17:40,070
Kim Tae Young, Choi Jin Cheul, and Hong Myung Bo...

553
00:17:40,540 --> 00:17:42,640
- The three of them were incredible. - They were so amazing.

554
00:17:42,880 --> 00:17:44,109
Even looking back today...

555
00:17:44,110 --> 00:17:45,979
- I mean, modern players are great. - Right.

556
00:17:45,980 --> 00:17:47,849
- But they were so tough... - Indeed.

557
00:17:47,850 --> 00:17:50,120
and really tenacious.

558
00:17:50,480 --> 00:17:54,250
Such defenders are hard to find.

559
00:17:54,350 --> 00:17:55,350
I'll explain to you.

560
00:17:55,620 --> 00:17:57,120
Hong Myung Bo had techniques.

561
00:17:57,860 --> 00:17:59,060
He used techniques.

562
00:17:59,120 --> 00:18:01,960
He wasn't strong, but very smart. He was a libero.

563
00:18:02,460 --> 00:18:05,399
Jin Cheul has both techniques and power.

564
00:18:05,400 --> 00:18:06,469
- He has both. - That's right.

565
00:18:06,470 --> 00:18:08,129
- What Tae Young was good at was... - Yes?

566
00:18:08,130 --> 00:18:09,400
He was fast.

567
00:18:09,600 --> 00:18:12,639
- The opposing attackers run fast. - Yes.

568
00:18:12,640 --> 00:18:13,740
So a defender should run fast too.

569
00:18:13,940 --> 00:18:15,039
He was also tough.

570
00:18:15,040 --> 00:18:16,579
He didn't care what the opposing players said.

571
00:18:16,580 --> 00:18:18,280
- He just kept running toward them. - That's right.

572
00:18:18,510 --> 00:18:20,049
Such traits of his were what made him...

573
00:18:20,050 --> 00:18:21,609
- a national team player. - That's right.

574
00:18:21,610 --> 00:18:23,150
He wasn't selected because he had good techniques.

575
00:18:23,250 --> 00:18:24,749
- But that's... - I agree with him on this.

576
00:18:24,750 --> 00:18:25,850
- I agree. - You agree?

577
00:18:26,050 --> 00:18:28,090
- He agrees. - His strong will to win?

578
00:18:28,550 --> 00:18:29,919
He was tough and fast.

579
00:18:29,920 --> 00:18:32,559
- That totally worked for him. - I bet he'll be back here soon.

580
00:18:32,560 --> 00:18:34,189
- No techniques. - You can't play soccer...

581
00:18:34,190 --> 00:18:36,260
unless you know how to kick a ball.

582
00:18:36,500 --> 00:18:37,629
- He's upset. - My gosh. Today...

583
00:18:37,630 --> 00:18:39,429
- Of course, he kicks a ball well. - Exactly.

584
00:18:39,430 --> 00:18:41,699
He's fast and tough on top of that. Am I right?

585
00:18:41,700 --> 00:18:43,940
- That's right. - His jersey number was even seven.

586
00:18:44,170 --> 00:18:46,539
- It's reserved for a good player. - That's right.

587
00:18:46,540 --> 00:18:48,569
- He was Korea's best center-back. - Exactly.

588
00:18:48,570 --> 00:18:50,810
Back then, we could get any number we wanted.

589
00:18:51,010 --> 00:18:53,680
- That's not true. - He said it was given to anyone.

590
00:18:53,910 --> 00:18:55,849
- Seok Ju, can you... - All right.

591
00:18:55,850 --> 00:18:58,350
beat Tae Young with your skills?

592
00:18:58,950 --> 00:19:00,550
Of course, even with one eye closed.

593
00:19:00,590 --> 00:19:02,090
- Really? - Are you serious?

594
00:19:02,120 --> 00:19:04,189
- I had good dribbling skills. - True.

595
00:19:04,190 --> 00:19:06,759
You must watch your opponent's feet when dribbling.

596
00:19:06,760 --> 00:19:07,830
- Right. - I see.

597
00:19:08,030 --> 00:19:09,359
- You'd beat him... - I'd beat him,

598
00:19:09,360 --> 00:19:10,959
- but say that I do. - Okay.

599
00:19:10,960 --> 00:19:12,060
He'd beat me up.

600
00:19:13,200 --> 00:19:15,030
- For real. - I was too scared to beat him.

601
00:19:15,670 --> 00:19:17,669
- You two are close. - That's a personal reason.

602
00:19:17,670 --> 00:19:19,400
- Would he hit you? - He scares me.

603
00:19:19,500 --> 00:19:22,039
You know how we have VAR right now?

604
00:19:22,040 --> 00:19:23,409
- Yes. - Say that we had it back then.

605
00:19:23,410 --> 00:19:25,080
Tae Young couldn't have played soccer.

606
00:19:26,210 --> 00:19:27,509
(A lucky guy born in the right era)

607
00:19:27,510 --> 00:19:28,849
- What do you mean by that? - Did Tae Young...

608
00:19:28,850 --> 00:19:30,119
beat others up...

609
00:19:30,120 --> 00:19:31,420
- where there were no CCTVs? - Right.

610
00:19:31,450 --> 00:19:32,479
- He would've been kicked out... - At blind spots.

611
00:19:32,480 --> 00:19:33,849
- of every game. - At blind spots.

612
00:19:33,850 --> 00:19:34,889
That'd be the end of the season.

613
00:19:34,890 --> 00:19:36,089
He'd be kicked out of every game. I'm serious.

614
00:19:36,090 --> 00:19:37,090
- I see. - A wrap-up?

615
00:19:37,091 --> 00:19:39,359
He does too many things when no one is watching.

616
00:19:39,360 --> 00:19:41,960
(The brutal acts he did while no one was watching)

617
00:19:42,630 --> 00:19:43,659
We've talked about...

618
00:19:43,660 --> 00:19:44,699
- being thrown out. - How funny.

619
00:19:44,700 --> 00:19:47,269
Now then, let's move on to the World Soccer Games.

620
00:19:47,270 --> 00:19:48,270
Okay.

621
00:19:48,271 --> 00:19:51,000
This time, we'll start with Seok Ju.

622
00:19:51,570 --> 00:19:53,769
- It's legendary. - True.

623
00:19:53,770 --> 00:19:54,869
Or should I say it's a dark past?

624
00:19:54,870 --> 00:19:56,809
The back tackle incident.

625
00:19:56,810 --> 00:19:58,980
- I remember. - It was an impressive one.

626
00:19:59,010 --> 00:20:00,279
- The Mexico match. - The Mexico match.

627
00:20:00,280 --> 00:20:01,309
- It was in 1998. - Correct.

628
00:20:01,310 --> 00:20:02,649
- In France. - Sports Events in Paris.

629
00:20:02,650 --> 00:20:04,449
- No, World Soccer Games in France. - It was paradise and the pit...

630
00:20:04,450 --> 00:20:06,689
- Right. - in that short period of time.

631
00:20:06,690 --> 00:20:09,149
He was the first Korean to score a goal.

632
00:20:09,150 --> 00:20:10,659
- Yes. - Everyone went wild.

633
00:20:10,660 --> 00:20:12,619
- In the World Soccer Games. - As soon as he cheered,

634
00:20:12,620 --> 00:20:14,029
- Soon after. - he was kicked out.

635
00:20:14,030 --> 00:20:15,929
The referee gave him a red card for the back tackle.

636
00:20:15,930 --> 00:20:17,599
I still remember it to this day.

637
00:20:17,600 --> 00:20:19,259
- It's been 30 years. - Correct.

638
00:20:19,260 --> 00:20:21,700
That's why we can look back on the situation calmly now.

639
00:20:21,930 --> 00:20:23,540
But I'm sure it was tough...

640
00:20:23,740 --> 00:20:25,769
- for Seok Ju himself. - Absolutely.

641
00:20:25,770 --> 00:20:27,539
- Because... - It must've been tough.

642
00:20:27,540 --> 00:20:29,240
the Red Devils...

643
00:20:29,370 --> 00:20:32,210
started online through Nownuri and Chollian.

644
00:20:32,580 --> 00:20:35,779
Back then, Seok Ju received a lifetime's worth of criticism.

645
00:20:35,780 --> 00:20:37,779
- People even looked back... - Yes.

646
00:20:37,780 --> 00:20:39,019
while walking, worrying...

647
00:20:39,020 --> 00:20:40,290
- Seok Ju might tackle them. - And...

648
00:20:40,820 --> 00:20:43,590
Even out of the blue at school.

649
00:20:43,860 --> 00:20:45,090
You'd just be standing there, right?

650
00:20:45,660 --> 00:20:47,230
"I'm Ha Seok Ju! Here's a back tackle!"

651
00:20:47,890 --> 00:20:48,959
- I remember. - That's how...

652
00:20:48,960 --> 00:20:50,029
we used to joke around...

653
00:20:50,030 --> 00:20:52,359
- at school. - Here.

654
00:20:52,360 --> 00:20:53,669
It's been 30 years.

655
00:20:53,670 --> 00:20:55,599
- Right. - Let him explain what happened.

656
00:20:55,600 --> 00:20:57,100
- Okay. - What happened?

657
00:20:58,200 --> 00:20:59,470
You guys are really having fun with this.

658
00:20:59,570 --> 00:21:01,239
(Just one back tackle is enough to make everyone's day.)

659
00:21:01,240 --> 00:21:02,709
- Now... - Come on.

660
00:21:02,710 --> 00:21:04,579
- We can laugh about it now. - I'm sure...

661
00:21:04,580 --> 00:21:06,039
- Yes. - everyone watched...

662
00:21:06,040 --> 00:21:07,549
the match against Mexico in...

663
00:21:07,550 --> 00:21:08,979
- Right. - the 1998 World Soccer Games.

664
00:21:08,980 --> 00:21:10,049
- Yes. - Of course.

665
00:21:10,050 --> 00:21:13,019
I should explain this first. Before that World Soccer Games,

666
00:21:13,020 --> 00:21:15,350
- players usually weren't given... - True.

667
00:21:15,420 --> 00:21:17,619
- red cards for back tackles. - No.

668
00:21:17,620 --> 00:21:20,589
- But starting in 1998, - The 1998 World Soccer Games.

669
00:21:20,590 --> 00:21:22,429
- with zero tolerance, - If your studs were showing.

670
00:21:22,430 --> 00:21:24,599
- The studs. - players would immediately get...

671
00:21:24,600 --> 00:21:25,959
a red card for tackling from behind,

672
00:21:25,960 --> 00:21:30,139
so the referees had become much stricter.

673
00:21:30,140 --> 00:21:31,539
- Back tackle. - Seok Ju...

674
00:21:31,540 --> 00:21:33,909
didn't really pay attention back then.

675
00:21:33,910 --> 00:21:36,380
The players...

676
00:21:36,580 --> 00:21:38,079
didn't think too deeply about it.

677
00:21:38,080 --> 00:21:39,539
- See that? He should've listened. - A back tackle...

678
00:21:39,540 --> 00:21:41,879
is when you hit a player from behind with both legs.

679
00:21:41,880 --> 00:21:43,079
(Back tackle: A dangerous tackle targeting the opponent's back legs)

680
00:21:43,080 --> 00:21:44,779
That was the first and last time...

681
00:21:44,780 --> 00:21:47,489
- I was ever sent off in a match. - Really?

682
00:21:47,490 --> 00:21:48,649
I was never sent off before or after that.

683
00:21:48,650 --> 00:21:49,990
- Oh, dear. - Here's the thing.

684
00:21:50,290 --> 00:21:51,919
It happened only...

685
00:21:51,920 --> 00:21:53,659
two or three minutes after I scored.

686
00:21:53,660 --> 00:21:54,859
When a goal is scored,

687
00:21:54,860 --> 00:21:56,029
- people get fired up. - Of course.

688
00:21:56,030 --> 00:21:57,400
- Even the players get excited. - True.

689
00:21:57,700 --> 00:22:00,770
When I think back on why I did that, even now,

690
00:22:01,130 --> 00:22:03,440
I can tell something felt off.

691
00:22:03,700 --> 00:22:05,770
There was no excuse...

692
00:22:06,300 --> 00:22:08,470
- for getting sent off. - Really?

693
00:22:08,510 --> 00:22:10,240
At that moment,

694
00:22:10,440 --> 00:22:11,739
- I was overflowing with energy... - Right.

695
00:22:11,740 --> 00:22:15,110
and thinking only about putting heavy pressure on the opponents.

696
00:22:15,780 --> 00:22:17,780
- But then I got a red card. - I remember.

697
00:22:18,320 --> 00:22:21,350
I asked, "Why?" But that was the only English word I knew.

698
00:22:21,990 --> 00:22:23,989
- The only English you knew? - "Why?"

699
00:22:23,990 --> 00:22:26,259
- Why? - "Why?"

700
00:22:26,260 --> 00:22:27,589
- Why? - It felt like...

701
00:22:27,590 --> 00:22:29,260
the whole field was spinning upside down.

702
00:22:29,360 --> 00:22:31,160
The field felt like it was turning upside down.

703
00:22:32,100 --> 00:22:34,270
That was when I got the red card.

704
00:22:35,300 --> 00:22:37,299
But I couldn't go to the stands. Sent-off players had to go...

705
00:22:37,300 --> 00:22:38,900
- to the locker room. - Immediately, right?

706
00:22:39,000 --> 00:22:40,769
There was nothing there. Not even a TV.

707
00:22:40,770 --> 00:22:41,910
Oh, no.

708
00:22:42,610 --> 00:22:45,380
Feeling guilty, I just sat there with my head down.

709
00:22:45,880 --> 00:22:47,649
After the first half, the players came back...

710
00:22:47,650 --> 00:22:49,010
and told me we were leading 1 to 0.

711
00:22:49,580 --> 00:22:51,850
- Right. - The coach, my teammates,

712
00:22:52,120 --> 00:22:53,350
and the younger players...

713
00:22:53,590 --> 00:22:56,389
- "Cheer up." - all tried to comfort me.

714
00:22:56,390 --> 00:22:58,220
But the second half...

715
00:22:58,660 --> 00:23:00,129
- was painful for me. - Of course.

716
00:23:00,130 --> 00:23:01,389
- Of course. - Gosh.

717
00:23:01,390 --> 00:23:03,199
I heard the crowd erupt three times...

718
00:23:03,200 --> 00:23:04,930
while I was alone in the locker room.

719
00:23:05,200 --> 00:23:06,700
The cheers were incredibly loud.

720
00:23:08,130 --> 00:23:10,199
(Seok Ju heard 3 cheers from the locker room...)

721
00:23:10,200 --> 00:23:12,270
(during the second half, all by himself.)

722
00:23:14,078 --> 00:23:16,848
Those three cheers broke my heart.

723
00:23:17,978 --> 00:23:19,348
It would've been better if I hadn't heard them.

724
00:23:19,948 --> 00:23:21,848
All I could think was,

725
00:23:22,218 --> 00:23:23,247
"If we score one more,"

726
00:23:23,248 --> 00:23:24,647
- "it'll be 2 to 2." - Right.

727
00:23:24,648 --> 00:23:26,088
"But if Mexico scores 3, we'll lose 3 to 1."

728
00:23:26,588 --> 00:23:28,057
"Now that I've been sent off,"

729
00:23:28,058 --> 00:23:30,288
"our chances of losing are higher than our chances of winning."

730
00:23:30,928 --> 00:23:33,097
When the players came back after the second half,

731
00:23:33,098 --> 00:23:34,458
every one of them had their heads down.

732
00:23:34,928 --> 00:23:37,268
- I realized it was three to one. - Three to one.

733
00:23:38,098 --> 00:23:40,067
For the next match against the Netherlands,

734
00:23:40,068 --> 00:23:41,097
- Right. - I watched from the stands.

735
00:23:41,098 --> 00:23:42,737
- We lost 5 to 0. - It was 5 to 0.

736
00:23:42,738 --> 00:23:44,508
Even Coach Cha Bum Kun got replaced.

737
00:23:45,008 --> 00:23:46,577
I had nowhere to go.

738
00:23:46,578 --> 00:23:47,908
- I felt completely lost. - Right.

739
00:23:48,338 --> 00:23:50,377
I couldn't eat at all.

740
00:23:50,378 --> 00:23:52,208
- So I didn't. - Everything tasted bland.

741
00:23:52,248 --> 00:23:53,948
You were suspended for two matches...

742
00:23:54,178 --> 00:23:56,078
- after getting a straight red card. - Right.

743
00:23:56,178 --> 00:23:57,288
Only for a straight red card.

744
00:23:57,348 --> 00:24:00,288
But FIFA showed me some leniency, so I was allowed to play one match.

745
00:24:00,858 --> 00:24:02,558
My final match was against Belgium.

746
00:24:02,588 --> 00:24:03,927
When I went back to my room,

747
00:24:03,928 --> 00:24:06,528
- the media was all about me. - Of course.

748
00:24:06,598 --> 00:24:08,898
The story was about sitting alone in my room without eating...

749
00:24:09,158 --> 00:24:10,728
Honestly, I didn't want to face anyone.

750
00:24:11,198 --> 00:24:12,598
In past World Soccer Games,

751
00:24:12,698 --> 00:24:14,268
some players got shot while leaving the field.

752
00:24:14,438 --> 00:24:15,937
- Yes, in Colombia. - Things like that happened.

753
00:24:15,938 --> 00:24:17,237
- I remember. - No way.

754
00:24:17,238 --> 00:24:19,937
- It happened in Colombia. - Yes, it did.

755
00:24:19,938 --> 00:24:21,837
- It's nothing to laugh about. - No.

756
00:24:21,838 --> 00:24:23,147
- Because... - There were a few.

757
00:24:23,148 --> 00:24:25,047
- Right. - But we can't own guns.

758
00:24:25,048 --> 00:24:26,078
- It was tough. - Here's the thing.

759
00:24:26,178 --> 00:24:28,618
But all I received were letters of encouragement.

760
00:24:29,118 --> 00:24:30,688
Nobody was criticizing me.

761
00:24:31,288 --> 00:24:33,258
I found out that only encouraging letters...

762
00:24:33,418 --> 00:24:35,657
were given to me. The rest were thrown away.

763
00:24:35,658 --> 00:24:36,658
(Friends and family gave him what would cheer him up.)

764
00:24:36,758 --> 00:24:38,158
That comforted me a little.

765
00:24:38,888 --> 00:24:40,727
Seok Ju, let's say that...

766
00:24:40,728 --> 00:24:42,558
- Right. - we had a time machine.

767
00:24:42,828 --> 00:24:45,168
You'd go back to the Mexico match, wouldn't you?

768
00:24:45,798 --> 00:24:48,068
(Accessing the past)

769
00:24:49,168 --> 00:24:50,437
I'd go back to before...

770
00:24:50,438 --> 00:24:53,107
getting kicked out after scoring the goal.

771
00:24:53,108 --> 00:24:55,008
What would've happened, Seok Ju? I can't help but wonder.

772
00:24:55,178 --> 00:24:56,178
Judging by the atmosphere,

773
00:24:56,179 --> 00:24:57,608
- couldn't we have won? - For real.

774
00:24:57,808 --> 00:25:00,378
If you hadn't been kicked out. I often think about it.

775
00:25:00,478 --> 00:25:02,318
Just by the atmosphere, we could've won.

776
00:25:02,778 --> 00:25:04,247
That's why I want to go back to before that.

777
00:25:04,248 --> 00:25:06,147
- Right. - It's the spirit.

778
00:25:06,148 --> 00:25:08,487
- I had several rough years. - Right.

779
00:25:08,488 --> 00:25:10,028
After that, I've been able...

780
00:25:10,128 --> 00:25:13,398
to talk about and listen to the back tackle with a light heart.

781
00:25:13,428 --> 00:25:16,628
Seok Ju, I heard players know if the ball will go in or not...

782
00:25:16,898 --> 00:25:19,868
when their foot comes in contact with the ball during a free kick.

783
00:25:19,998 --> 00:25:21,667
The kickers are already fixed...

784
00:25:21,668 --> 00:25:25,268
for the free kick depending on the distance from the goalpost.

785
00:25:25,608 --> 00:25:26,677
Who kicks the ball.

786
00:25:26,678 --> 00:25:27,738
- We're set in order. - I see.

787
00:25:27,778 --> 00:25:29,178
It wasn't a distance I could kick.

788
00:25:29,578 --> 00:25:30,908
Yoo Sang Chul kicked the long distance.

789
00:25:31,348 --> 00:25:34,018
The close distance, 16m to 20m, was Ko Jong Soo and me.

790
00:25:34,348 --> 00:25:35,648
It was all fixed.

791
00:25:35,748 --> 00:25:38,718
- The goalpost was about 25m away. - Right.

792
00:25:38,888 --> 00:25:40,688
I was the senior.

793
00:25:40,958 --> 00:25:43,427
I told him I wanted to kick the ball. He couldn't talk back.

794
00:25:43,428 --> 00:25:45,258
The order of rank...

795
00:25:45,388 --> 00:25:47,127
- Strict? - was strict back then.

796
00:25:47,128 --> 00:25:49,967
- He shouldn't have kicked it. - As it was 25m away...

797
00:25:49,968 --> 00:25:51,067
If he hadn't made the goal.

798
00:25:51,068 --> 00:25:52,968
He shouldn't have kicked the free kick,

799
00:25:53,098 --> 00:25:54,537
but he did.

800
00:25:54,538 --> 00:25:56,407
(Cutting in out of the blue)

801
00:25:56,408 --> 00:25:59,268
- If he hadn't scored... - Don't get angry.

802
00:25:59,408 --> 00:26:00,807
If he hadn't scored, he wouldn't have had...

803
00:26:00,808 --> 00:26:02,777
- that adrenaline rush. - Exactly.

804
00:26:02,778 --> 00:26:04,907
There wouldn't have been the back tackle.

805
00:26:04,908 --> 00:26:06,517
Korea would've won.

806
00:26:06,518 --> 00:26:07,518
- Of course. - Right.

807
00:26:07,519 --> 00:26:09,278
Honestly, I shouldn't have kicked it.

808
00:26:10,088 --> 00:26:11,987
(The best scene yet, the worst mistake of a lifetime)

809
00:26:11,988 --> 00:26:14,817
Because I kicked the ball hard...

810
00:26:14,818 --> 00:26:16,757
Seok Ju, you were an audience member...

811
00:26:16,758 --> 00:26:18,658
during the 2002 World Soccer Games, right?

812
00:26:18,688 --> 00:26:20,797
Didn't you ever wish how great...

813
00:26:20,798 --> 00:26:22,858
it would've been if you had been a player?

814
00:26:22,898 --> 00:26:26,098
I trained under Coach Hiddink for several months.

815
00:26:26,198 --> 00:26:30,067
But I had issues with my physical strength.

816
00:26:30,068 --> 00:26:32,667
- Right. - But putting aside that issue,

817
00:26:32,668 --> 00:26:35,108
I told Coach Park Hang Seo first.

818
00:26:35,878 --> 00:26:37,078
"I'm too scared."

819
00:26:37,708 --> 00:26:40,078
Getting kicked off because of the back tackle in 1998.

820
00:26:40,418 --> 00:26:42,578
It scared me, and I had lost all confidence.

821
00:26:42,878 --> 00:26:44,518
- Right. - Back then, weren't you already...

822
00:26:44,718 --> 00:26:46,118
- Thirty-six. - Thirty-six.

823
00:26:46,148 --> 00:26:48,388
Myung Bo and Sun Hong are a year younger than me.

824
00:26:48,758 --> 00:26:51,627
I was one of the Be the Reds supporters...

825
00:26:51,628 --> 00:26:54,858
at their first match against Poland in Busan.

826
00:26:56,028 --> 00:26:58,367
As I'm human myself, I had mixed feelings...

827
00:26:58,368 --> 00:27:01,067
- and thought, "What if..." - Of course.

828
00:27:01,068 --> 00:27:03,238
- As a player. - "I were one of the players?"

829
00:27:03,538 --> 00:27:05,107
- The 1998 incident. - I was...

830
00:27:05,108 --> 00:27:06,708
in the national team for 11 years,

831
00:27:07,238 --> 00:27:09,307
but people know players who were only in the team for one year...

832
00:27:09,308 --> 00:27:11,377
- during the 2002 Soccer Games. - Right.

833
00:27:11,378 --> 00:27:13,378
That breaks my heart.

834
00:27:13,748 --> 00:27:15,078
But it can't be helped.

835
00:27:15,848 --> 00:27:17,888
- After the Mexico match, - Yes?

836
00:27:18,048 --> 00:27:19,788
acrostic poems using Ha Seok Ju's name...

837
00:27:19,888 --> 00:27:22,317
were trending on soccer community boards.

838
00:27:22,318 --> 00:27:23,427
- Really? - Yes.

839
00:27:23,428 --> 00:27:24,787
I brought a few.

840
00:27:24,788 --> 00:27:26,027
You remember them, don't you?

841
00:27:26,028 --> 00:27:27,028
I do.

842
00:27:27,029 --> 00:27:28,598
Why don't you start us off?

843
00:27:28,958 --> 00:27:30,598
- H. - Hit one goal.

844
00:27:31,528 --> 00:27:32,798
- It's already funny. - S.

845
00:27:32,968 --> 00:27:34,038
Surrendered three.

846
00:27:34,498 --> 00:27:36,338
- J. - Just unbelievable.

847
00:27:37,208 --> 00:27:38,968
What a clever one.

848
00:27:39,138 --> 00:27:41,407
- I remember. - Yes, it's real.

849
00:27:41,408 --> 00:27:43,077
Acrostic poems were a thing back then.

850
00:27:43,078 --> 00:27:44,078
Totally.

851
00:27:44,079 --> 00:27:45,778
Aren't you a member of the Garrincha Club?

852
00:27:46,148 --> 00:27:47,918
- Garrincha Club. - Garrincha...

853
00:27:48,018 --> 00:27:49,147
was a world-renowned...

854
00:27:49,148 --> 00:27:50,447
- Player. - Brazilian soccer player.

855
00:27:50,448 --> 00:27:53,558
Members of the Garrincha Club are...

856
00:27:53,858 --> 00:27:54,917
- those who were kicked out... - Kicked out...

857
00:27:54,918 --> 00:27:56,388
- right away. - right after scoring a goal.

858
00:27:56,488 --> 00:27:57,957
- Is that the Garrincha Club? - There was Zidane.

859
00:27:57,958 --> 00:27:59,457
- In one match. - The World Soccer Games.

860
00:27:59,458 --> 00:28:01,157
- Ronaldinho. - Ronaldinho and Zidane.

861
00:28:01,158 --> 00:28:03,058
He's in the same club as world-famous players.

862
00:28:03,768 --> 00:28:05,528
Soo Geun, read that out loud for us.

863
00:28:06,168 --> 00:28:08,238
- As Jang Hoon mentioned earlier, - Yes?

864
00:28:08,398 --> 00:28:10,707
Garrincha was a great Brazilian soccer player.

865
00:28:10,708 --> 00:28:11,737
What's the sent-off reason?

866
00:28:11,738 --> 00:28:13,478
"A foul unrelated to the play."

867
00:28:14,208 --> 00:28:15,937
- Back then... - Players were passing over there,

868
00:28:15,938 --> 00:28:17,808
but he beat others up on this side.

869
00:28:18,078 --> 00:28:19,707
- Listen. - A dangerous player.

870
00:28:19,708 --> 00:28:20,947
The same goes with Zidane.

871
00:28:20,948 --> 00:28:23,077
- He literally just hit people. - It was unrelated.

872
00:28:23,078 --> 00:28:24,917
Ha Seok Ju was the last player to be sent off...

873
00:28:24,918 --> 00:28:26,248
- with a single red card. - Right.

874
00:28:26,318 --> 00:28:27,857
- Diao was sent off due to... - Accumulated warnings.

875
00:28:27,858 --> 00:28:29,057
accumulated warnings.

876
00:28:29,058 --> 00:28:30,058
As for Ronaldinho...

877
00:28:30,088 --> 00:28:32,187
- He steps on his opponents' ankles. - The opponents' ankles.

878
00:28:32,188 --> 00:28:33,497
- Gosh. - The ankles.

879
00:28:33,498 --> 00:28:35,227
- Zidane is famous. - Zidane is so famous.

880
00:28:35,228 --> 00:28:37,267
- With his forehead. - Yes.

881
00:28:37,268 --> 00:28:38,927
He headbutted the opponent with his forehead...

882
00:28:38,928 --> 00:28:40,367
- and got sent off. - Yes.

883
00:28:40,368 --> 00:28:42,167
Gosh, Aboubakar of Cameroon is so...

884
00:28:42,168 --> 00:28:43,837
It was for repeatedly taking his shirt off after scoring.

885
00:28:43,838 --> 00:28:45,607
He should have done it once,

886
00:28:45,608 --> 00:28:46,608
- but he did it twice. - It was twice.

887
00:28:46,608 --> 00:28:47,608
It was twice.

888
00:28:47,609 --> 00:28:49,777
If it's one time, it's a yellow card.

889
00:28:49,778 --> 00:28:51,477
- They do goal ceremonies. - Yes.

890
00:28:51,478 --> 00:28:53,147
Even in the past, we could see that...

891
00:28:53,148 --> 00:28:55,117
they run after the one who scored to catch them...

892
00:28:55,118 --> 00:28:56,248
- when they make a goal. - Yes.

893
00:28:56,588 --> 00:28:57,617
And the one who scored...

894
00:28:57,618 --> 00:28:58,618
- runs away as well. - Right.

895
00:28:58,619 --> 00:29:01,587
- That's right. - Why do they want to catch him?

896
00:29:01,588 --> 00:29:04,187
These guys are the goalkeeper and defender,

897
00:29:04,188 --> 00:29:05,887
so they don't get the chance to make a goal.

898
00:29:05,888 --> 00:29:08,998
They won't know what you're talking about.

899
00:29:10,098 --> 00:29:11,098
Is that so?

900
00:29:11,598 --> 00:29:13,397
- Gosh. - You're the only one who knows?

901
00:29:13,398 --> 00:29:14,467
- I've made tons of goals. - You only know that?

902
00:29:14,468 --> 00:29:16,167
- Sure. - Yes, he made tons of goals.

903
00:29:16,168 --> 00:29:17,468
- When you score, - Yes.

904
00:29:18,008 --> 00:29:19,207
you need to head to the main stand.

905
00:29:19,208 --> 00:29:20,208
To the main stand?

906
00:29:20,209 --> 00:29:22,837
You need to face the main stand.

907
00:29:22,838 --> 00:29:24,308
If you go the other way, you're only showing your back.

908
00:29:25,048 --> 00:29:26,877
- Show the camera. - So that the camera sees you?

909
00:29:26,878 --> 00:29:29,377
And before the team catches you, you need to run away.

910
00:29:29,378 --> 00:29:30,717
If you get caught, the camera won't see you.

911
00:29:30,718 --> 00:29:32,617
Is that why?

912
00:29:32,618 --> 00:29:34,857
That's why they become faster after making the goal.

913
00:29:34,858 --> 00:29:37,257
- Even faster? - Full sprint.

914
00:29:37,258 --> 00:29:38,258
Full speed ahead...

915
00:29:38,259 --> 00:29:39,287
- to the front and get filmed, - They are so fast.

916
00:29:39,288 --> 00:29:40,797
and then...

917
00:29:40,798 --> 00:29:43,058
Sometimes, they even get cramps from running.

918
00:29:43,728 --> 00:29:45,267
- That's quite dangerous. - Like this.

919
00:29:45,268 --> 00:29:46,737
Some get hurt.

920
00:29:46,738 --> 00:29:48,437
Even the goalkeeper runs out sometimes.

921
00:29:48,438 --> 00:29:49,567
To get caught on camera.

922
00:29:49,568 --> 00:29:50,568
Do you go out there often?

923
00:29:50,569 --> 00:29:52,367
I do, during important games.

924
00:29:52,368 --> 00:29:54,407
He doesn't even have to say it.

925
00:29:54,408 --> 00:29:55,907
I'm sure he went all the way across to the opponent's goal.

926
00:29:55,908 --> 00:29:58,277
- For sure. - In the past, on newspapers,

927
00:29:58,278 --> 00:29:59,607
- when they made a goal, - Right.

928
00:29:59,608 --> 00:30:00,617
- you could see the team members... - Right.

929
00:30:00,618 --> 00:30:01,647
- next to them. - Right.

930
00:30:01,648 --> 00:30:04,348
- Yes. - They are made into scrapbooks.

931
00:30:05,018 --> 00:30:06,857
And if you're not quick enough,

932
00:30:06,858 --> 00:30:08,918
it could end before you get there.

933
00:30:09,888 --> 00:30:11,757
- That's why they run so fast? - It could end.

934
00:30:11,758 --> 00:30:12,887
- To be in the newspaper? - It will be too late.

935
00:30:12,888 --> 00:30:14,097
They need to be...

936
00:30:14,098 --> 00:30:16,727
They should always be near Seok Ju.

937
00:30:16,728 --> 00:30:17,967
- Like this. - They must be close by.

938
00:30:17,968 --> 00:30:19,467
The secret is finally revealed.

939
00:30:19,468 --> 00:30:23,407
To be honest, with back tackles and things like that,

940
00:30:23,408 --> 00:30:25,738
Tae Young is quite aggressive at defending.

941
00:30:26,068 --> 00:30:27,437
- Yes. - But Tae Young...

942
00:30:27,438 --> 00:30:29,937
- has never been thrown out. - Really?

943
00:30:29,938 --> 00:30:31,777
- He has been thrown out. - Is that true?

944
00:30:31,778 --> 00:30:34,047
During the 2000 Korea versus Japan match,

945
00:30:34,048 --> 00:30:36,418
I was the one who scored the goal with my left foot...

946
00:30:36,518 --> 00:30:37,787
in Jamsil,

947
00:30:37,788 --> 00:30:39,047
- after hitting the goal post. - I remember that.

948
00:30:39,048 --> 00:30:40,288
- That was amazing. - In front of 80,000 spectators.

949
00:30:40,788 --> 00:30:43,487
He got thrown out around 25 minutes into the second half.

950
00:30:43,488 --> 00:30:44,927
- Yes. - Is that true, Tae Young?

951
00:30:44,928 --> 00:30:46,587
We won with one player missing.

952
00:30:46,588 --> 00:30:47,927
- Gosh. - It was a record.

953
00:30:47,928 --> 00:30:49,027
He won, so why did I lose?

954
00:30:49,028 --> 00:30:50,028
No one...

955
00:30:50,268 --> 00:30:52,467
- How did it turn out that way? - That's...

956
00:30:52,468 --> 00:30:54,297
- No one remembers it. - I don't remember.

957
00:30:54,298 --> 00:30:56,807
- That must be so... - I don't remember.

958
00:30:56,808 --> 00:30:59,037
That was the 2000 Korea versus Japan match.

959
00:30:59,038 --> 00:31:00,277
- It was a very big match. - Sure.

960
00:31:00,278 --> 00:31:02,037
- We don't remember that one... - In front of 80,000 spectators?

961
00:31:02,038 --> 00:31:03,507
- because we won. - You scored a goal.

962
00:31:03,508 --> 00:31:04,777
- I lost. - Yes.

963
00:31:04,778 --> 00:31:05,947
He won.

964
00:31:05,948 --> 00:31:07,447
No one has a problem with him.

965
00:31:07,448 --> 00:31:08,817
- Because he won. - Yes.

966
00:31:08,818 --> 00:31:10,348
If they had lost, he would have been gone as well.

967
00:31:10,548 --> 00:31:12,517
- "Gone?" - I don't think he remembers.

968
00:31:12,518 --> 00:31:13,687
- Gone, like this. - But...

969
00:31:13,688 --> 00:31:16,187
Seok Ju, if I recall,

970
00:31:16,188 --> 00:31:18,527
- your style wasn't tough. - No.

971
00:31:18,528 --> 00:31:19,827
- No. - He's a technique guy.

972
00:31:19,828 --> 00:31:23,027
- You made one tackle, - I know.

973
00:31:23,028 --> 00:31:24,367
- and that... - That ruined him at once.

974
00:31:24,368 --> 00:31:26,227
- I know. - But Tae Young...

975
00:31:26,228 --> 00:31:28,567
is an aggressive defender,

976
00:31:28,568 --> 00:31:31,038
so I assumed that he would have been thrown out more.

977
00:31:31,208 --> 00:31:33,377
You're saying that was the only time you were thrown out?

978
00:31:33,378 --> 00:31:35,007
- Yes. - How did you play...

979
00:31:35,008 --> 00:31:36,037
- to avoid that? - In Korea...

980
00:31:36,038 --> 00:31:38,707
- He plays smart. - In the K League,

981
00:31:38,708 --> 00:31:40,547
- the referees are Korean. - Yes.

982
00:31:40,548 --> 00:31:42,917
So if I make a foul, I would quickly go over and say,

983
00:31:42,918 --> 00:31:45,487
"I'm sorry," and help the opponent up.

984
00:31:45,488 --> 00:31:46,617
- And pat his back. - Apologizing?

985
00:31:46,618 --> 00:31:49,557
Soo Geun, you just said that he avoided it because he's smart,

986
00:31:49,558 --> 00:31:50,758
- right? - Yes.

987
00:31:51,028 --> 00:31:52,028
That's not true.

988
00:31:52,258 --> 00:31:53,258
(His nonstop roasting at Tae Young continues again.)

989
00:31:53,259 --> 00:31:54,797
- All of a sudden? - He's not smart, and...

990
00:31:54,798 --> 00:31:56,527
If they had had VAR back then,

991
00:31:56,528 --> 00:31:57,567
- he would have been thrown out... - I agree.

992
00:31:57,568 --> 00:31:58,597
more than 100 times.

993
00:31:58,598 --> 00:31:59,598
At every game.

994
00:31:59,599 --> 00:32:02,197
It's such a relief that he played before VAR existed.

995
00:32:02,198 --> 00:32:03,407
- Seriously. - Is that so?

996
00:32:03,408 --> 00:32:05,067
- That's the answer. - It's true.

997
00:32:05,068 --> 00:32:06,637
No, if there had been VAR back then,

998
00:32:06,638 --> 00:32:08,207
Tae Young would have adjusted to that.

999
00:32:08,208 --> 00:32:09,707
- That's it, Soo Geun. - That's it.

1000
00:32:09,708 --> 00:32:11,408
- Sure. - He's not that smart.

1001
00:32:11,708 --> 00:32:13,047
- Come on. - He's right.

1002
00:32:13,048 --> 00:32:15,047
- That's the answer. - He's not that smart.

1003
00:32:15,048 --> 00:32:16,817
Then did you make that tackle...

1004
00:32:16,818 --> 00:32:18,318
because you were so smart?

1005
00:32:18,988 --> 00:32:21,618
(Striking a weak point)

1006
00:32:22,758 --> 00:32:24,287
- Gosh. - Look at him.

1007
00:32:24,288 --> 00:32:26,657
- Is that why? - I'm actually...

1008
00:32:26,658 --> 00:32:27,898
I'm not smart.

1009
00:32:28,628 --> 00:32:30,467
Why are you admitting that?

1010
00:32:30,468 --> 00:32:32,767
Young Kwang keeps chiming in from the side.

1011
00:32:32,768 --> 00:32:34,467
- It's because... - Amazing.

1012
00:32:34,468 --> 00:32:36,637
When I first joined the professional team,

1013
00:32:36,638 --> 00:32:38,538
the defender in front of me was Tae Young.

1014
00:32:38,908 --> 00:32:40,007
I was the youngest,

1015
00:32:40,008 --> 00:32:41,037
and he was the oldest.

1016
00:32:41,038 --> 00:32:42,707
So I always saw him in front of me.

1017
00:32:42,708 --> 00:32:43,708
(Youngest Young Kwang, Oldest Tae Young)

1018
00:32:44,008 --> 00:32:45,308
I felt bad for the striker.

1019
00:32:45,678 --> 00:32:47,177
- Is that so? - Really?

1020
00:32:47,178 --> 00:32:49,417
When there was a corner kick, he would go nearby...

1021
00:32:49,418 --> 00:32:51,248
and hit the striker's thighs from behind with his knees.

1022
00:32:51,818 --> 00:32:52,818
- Really? - Yes.

1023
00:32:52,819 --> 00:32:54,387
- It was this, not my knees. - Really?

1024
00:32:54,388 --> 00:32:56,517
Yes, he would poke the ribs with this.

1025
00:32:56,518 --> 00:32:57,928
- Really? - I'm serious.

1026
00:32:58,158 --> 00:32:59,787
- Like this. - How would he do that?

1027
00:32:59,788 --> 00:33:00,997
If this is during the corner kick,

1028
00:33:00,998 --> 00:33:02,227
- the ball would come here. - Yes.

1029
00:33:02,228 --> 00:33:03,468
- I'll be the striker. - You're the striker.

1030
00:33:03,828 --> 00:33:05,628
- Watch my hand. - Okay.

1031
00:33:07,638 --> 00:33:09,638
(Pinching)

1032
00:33:10,468 --> 00:33:12,007
- Wait. - What?

1033
00:33:12,008 --> 00:33:14,137
Did he really do that?

1034
00:33:14,138 --> 00:33:15,907
This is just ten percent of the strength.

1035
00:33:15,908 --> 00:33:17,178
- Really? - Yes.

1036
00:33:17,308 --> 00:33:19,547
- And... - And how would he do the thighs?

1037
00:33:19,548 --> 00:33:22,047
- And when the striker reacts, - Yes.

1038
00:33:22,048 --> 00:33:23,947
- If he tries to go. - the defender follows a bit later,

1039
00:33:23,948 --> 00:33:26,017
- Yes. - so I need to stop him.

1040
00:33:26,018 --> 00:33:27,088
- Yes. - Like this.

1041
00:33:28,558 --> 00:33:29,558
Wait a minute.

1042
00:33:29,588 --> 00:33:30,658
(Poking)

1043
00:33:31,728 --> 00:33:33,627
- Wait a minute. - You would poke his back?

1044
00:33:33,628 --> 00:33:34,957
- Then is that... - During the corner kick?

1045
00:33:34,958 --> 00:33:37,227
The striker flinches and misses the timing.

1046
00:33:37,228 --> 00:33:38,327
- That's it. - I see.

1047
00:33:38,328 --> 00:33:39,897
He cuts off the timing of when they should go.

1048
00:33:39,898 --> 00:33:40,997
I will tell you everything.

1049
00:33:40,998 --> 00:33:43,267
Many foreign players of the K League were recruited in...

1050
00:33:43,268 --> 00:33:44,767
- with expensive contracts. - Yes.

1051
00:33:44,768 --> 00:33:46,837
He was the one who sent over half of them back home.

1052
00:33:46,838 --> 00:33:50,308
(Tae Young sent over half of them back home.)

1053
00:33:50,548 --> 00:33:52,907
That was nice.

1054
00:33:52,908 --> 00:33:55,377
- He sent them home? - It's true.

1055
00:33:55,378 --> 00:33:57,347
When the season ends, it's the end,

1056
00:33:57,348 --> 00:33:59,018
so they all head home.

1057
00:33:59,388 --> 00:34:00,487
They really went home.

1058
00:34:00,488 --> 00:34:01,717
They went without renewing the contract?

1059
00:34:01,718 --> 00:34:03,787
- They said, "No!" - They all went home after rehab.

1060
00:34:03,788 --> 00:34:06,287
- But... - That's why they went home?

1061
00:34:06,288 --> 00:34:08,227
In the world of sports,

1062
00:34:08,228 --> 00:34:09,558
when your opponent is...

1063
00:34:09,958 --> 00:34:11,297
someone like Tae Young,

1064
00:34:11,298 --> 00:34:12,627
- That's tough. - it's so...

1065
00:34:12,628 --> 00:34:14,367
- annoying, - Right.

1066
00:34:14,368 --> 00:34:15,497
- and you hate it, - Right.

1067
00:34:15,498 --> 00:34:16,797
- but if he's on our team, - Yes.

1068
00:34:16,798 --> 00:34:17,867
- you love it. - You love it.

1069
00:34:17,868 --> 00:34:19,037
- Yes. - Sure.

1070
00:34:19,038 --> 00:34:22,537
- He's hard to deal with, - Yes.

1071
00:34:22,538 --> 00:34:25,077
so it's great for your team.

1072
00:34:25,078 --> 00:34:26,507
But it's tough if he's your opponent.

1073
00:34:26,508 --> 00:34:29,078
Young Kwang is exaggerating a bit...

1074
00:34:29,318 --> 00:34:30,318
since this is a variety show,

1075
00:34:30,319 --> 00:34:31,547
but he was a great defender, right?

1076
00:34:31,548 --> 00:34:32,587
It must have been great to have the support.

1077
00:34:32,588 --> 00:34:34,558
But I was always so worried that he would get thrown out.

1078
00:34:35,818 --> 00:34:37,587
It would also be hard for him if Tae Young...

1079
00:34:37,588 --> 00:34:39,587
- isn't standing in front. - If he got caught...

1080
00:34:39,588 --> 00:34:40,697
He just hadn't got caught,

1081
00:34:40,698 --> 00:34:42,027
but if he had got caught, it would have been...

1082
00:34:42,028 --> 00:34:43,767
It's such a relief that...

1083
00:34:43,768 --> 00:34:44,867
- VAR didn't exist. - It's a red card, for sure.

1084
00:34:44,868 --> 00:34:45,868
Is it?

1085
00:34:45,869 --> 00:34:46,897
- You should have told the referee, - It's a red card, for sure?

1086
00:34:46,898 --> 00:34:47,898
- Young Kwang. - It was...

1087
00:34:49,138 --> 00:34:51,037
I did feel guilty as well,

1088
00:34:51,038 --> 00:34:52,138
so I was...

1089
00:34:52,668 --> 00:34:54,977
But he's smart...

1090
00:34:54,978 --> 00:34:56,837
because he knows when they are looking and when they aren't.

1091
00:34:56,838 --> 00:34:58,747
- Sure. - You need to get the timing right.

1092
00:34:58,748 --> 00:35:01,547
- That's not smart, though. - Young Kwang, you said that...

1093
00:35:01,548 --> 00:35:03,647
- Did you get a red card as well? - Did you ever get one?

1094
00:35:03,648 --> 00:35:05,618
I was the Top Dog of Suncheon.

1095
00:35:05,918 --> 00:35:07,918
But I kept bringing that to the soccer field,

1096
00:35:08,418 --> 00:35:10,627
so I ended up fighting a lot with the spectators and fans.

1097
00:35:10,628 --> 00:35:12,757
- Gosh, you shouldn't do that. - Why would you fight with them?

1098
00:35:12,758 --> 00:35:14,227
I threw water bottles at fans.

1099
00:35:14,228 --> 00:35:16,257
- Did you? - You're not smart, either.

1100
00:35:16,258 --> 00:35:18,597
Because you hear all the sounds from the stands.

1101
00:35:18,598 --> 00:35:19,797
- He's the goalkeeper. - Yes.

1102
00:35:19,798 --> 00:35:22,337
So I got a lot of red cards...

1103
00:35:22,338 --> 00:35:23,467
for those bad things.

1104
00:35:23,468 --> 00:35:24,937
- During the game? - During the game.

1105
00:35:24,938 --> 00:35:26,207
Like getting in a fight with the referee.

1106
00:35:26,208 --> 00:35:27,237
You lost control of your temper?

1107
00:35:27,238 --> 00:35:28,238
I couldn't control my temper.

1108
00:35:28,239 --> 00:35:30,977
As an athlete, you need self-control and wisdom.

1109
00:35:30,978 --> 00:35:32,077
- Yes. - Yes.

1110
00:35:32,078 --> 00:35:33,817
I don't think he's one to be an athlete,

1111
00:35:33,818 --> 00:35:34,818
but he did, so...

1112
00:35:34,819 --> 00:35:36,818
(He's not one to be an athlete.)

1113
00:35:37,218 --> 00:35:39,217
He doesn't have the personality to be an athlete.

1114
00:35:39,218 --> 00:35:40,218
- He doesn't have the personality? - No.

1115
00:35:40,219 --> 00:35:41,858
- His overall character? - His character?

1116
00:35:42,058 --> 00:35:43,757
He has bad character?

1117
00:35:43,758 --> 00:35:45,487
He can't even make it in.

1118
00:35:45,488 --> 00:35:46,657
- He can't make it in? - Honestly.

1119
00:35:46,658 --> 00:35:48,257
What about Tae Young?

1120
00:35:48,258 --> 00:35:49,497
Tae Young is smart.

1121
00:35:49,498 --> 00:35:51,397
- Is that so? - All of a sudden?

1122
00:35:51,398 --> 00:35:53,198
- He made it. - I roasted him,

1123
00:35:53,468 --> 00:35:54,668
and he joined right in.

1124
00:35:55,898 --> 00:35:57,967
- You need to be careful. - I think I should be nice to him.

1125
00:35:57,968 --> 00:35:59,637
- Yes. - It will come right back.

1126
00:35:59,638 --> 00:36:00,707
Next.

1127
00:36:00,708 --> 00:36:01,737
That's amazing.

1128
00:36:01,738 --> 00:36:02,877
- Gosh, that's so funny. - We're talking...

1129
00:36:02,878 --> 00:36:03,977
about World Soccer Games,

1130
00:36:03,978 --> 00:36:05,947
- and we can't leave this out. - No.

1131
00:36:05,948 --> 00:36:07,848
Tae Young wrote "Tiger Mask."

1132
00:36:08,048 --> 00:36:09,477
- That. - In 2002.

1133
00:36:09,478 --> 00:36:12,187
- Seok Ju was in the Garrincha Club, - Yes.

1134
00:36:12,188 --> 00:36:15,187
but Tae Young was in the Century Club.

1135
00:36:15,188 --> 00:36:16,818
- Yes. - Century Club.

1136
00:36:17,528 --> 00:36:19,827
If you play in more than 100 games at the A international matches,

1137
00:36:19,828 --> 00:36:22,227
- you make the Century Club. - Century Club.

1138
00:36:22,228 --> 00:36:23,968
It has the same "Club," but it feels different.

1139
00:36:24,928 --> 00:36:26,567
- Garrincha Club and Century Club. - Yes.

1140
00:36:26,568 --> 00:36:27,897
- It's very different. - Seok Ju...

1141
00:36:27,898 --> 00:36:29,767
You didn't make 100 games, Seok Ju?

1142
00:36:29,768 --> 00:36:31,567
- I made 94 games. - Gosh.

1143
00:36:31,568 --> 00:36:32,767
That's just six games short.

1144
00:36:32,768 --> 00:36:34,577
Can't you ask them...

1145
00:36:34,578 --> 00:36:36,737
to let you play six more games?

1146
00:36:36,738 --> 00:36:39,777
There's something these guys don't realize.

1147
00:36:39,778 --> 00:36:42,477
I went to the International Sports Events, as a wild card...

1148
00:36:42,478 --> 00:36:44,087
with Hwang Sun Hong and Lee Lim Saeng.

1149
00:36:44,088 --> 00:36:45,848
That's why I missed about ten games.

1150
00:36:46,448 --> 00:36:48,157
The International Sports Events don't count as the A match.

1151
00:36:48,158 --> 00:36:49,158
That's right.

1152
00:36:49,159 --> 00:36:50,427
So I couldn't complete it.

1153
00:36:50,428 --> 00:36:52,587
That was for the country, right?

1154
00:36:52,588 --> 00:36:53,757
I had no choice.

1155
00:36:53,758 --> 00:36:56,057
Getting chosen as the wild card is an honor.

1156
00:36:56,058 --> 00:36:57,667
Tae Young's keyword, "Tiger Mask,"

1157
00:36:57,668 --> 00:36:59,097
is for the 2002 World Soccer Games,

1158
00:36:59,098 --> 00:37:01,038
legendary semifinal run.

1159
00:37:01,738 --> 00:37:03,467
- It was amazing back then. - He's a fast runner,

1160
00:37:03,468 --> 00:37:04,468
but he's slower than me.

1161
00:37:05,768 --> 00:37:07,407
- It's true. - What are you saying?

1162
00:37:07,408 --> 00:37:08,537
Really?

1163
00:37:08,538 --> 00:37:10,447
- I was around 11 seconds, - Are you sure about it?

1164
00:37:10,448 --> 00:37:11,448
and he was around 12 seconds.

1165
00:37:12,048 --> 00:37:13,647
He was really in the 11-second range.

1166
00:37:13,648 --> 00:37:15,617
When Seok Ju was a player,

1167
00:37:15,618 --> 00:37:18,117
he didn't seem so fast.

1168
00:37:18,118 --> 00:37:20,217
- He runs with short steps. - His legs are short, so he...

1169
00:37:20,218 --> 00:37:22,287
- doesn't look fast, but he is. - I ran fastest at the 30m lane.

1170
00:37:22,288 --> 00:37:23,557
- His legs? - But I mean...

1171
00:37:23,558 --> 00:37:25,327
His legs are short, so he has to go like this.

1172
00:37:25,328 --> 00:37:26,427
- He used techniques... - So he doesn't look fast.

1173
00:37:26,428 --> 00:37:30,158
He seemed like a player focused on technique.

1174
00:37:30,628 --> 00:37:32,197
I have good technique, and I'm fast.

1175
00:37:32,198 --> 00:37:33,497
- He was fast. - Yes.

1176
00:37:33,498 --> 00:37:34,597
Why are you saying like that?

1177
00:37:34,598 --> 00:37:36,337
Speed is important with defenders.

1178
00:37:36,338 --> 00:37:37,738
Tae Young was really fast.

1179
00:37:38,408 --> 00:37:40,837
When I played with the mask on,

1180
00:37:40,838 --> 00:37:43,137
- It must feel stuffy. - it blocks my view.

1181
00:37:43,138 --> 00:37:44,207
And it vibrates your bones.

1182
00:37:44,208 --> 00:37:46,277
And I had to hit the headers...

1183
00:37:46,278 --> 00:37:48,748
with the mask on, since I'm a defender.

1184
00:37:49,048 --> 00:37:51,917
Every time I hit the header, the mask would move...

1185
00:37:51,918 --> 00:37:54,287
- and hit the place... - Right.

1186
00:37:54,288 --> 00:37:56,318
where my nose was broken, making it hurt.

1187
00:37:56,558 --> 00:37:58,887
I played while crying at that time.

1188
00:37:58,888 --> 00:38:00,897
Was it your decision?

1189
00:38:00,898 --> 00:38:02,327
Sure, it was my decision.

1190
00:38:02,328 --> 00:38:04,798
Back when I broke my nose...

1191
00:38:04,998 --> 00:38:07,538
When you break your nose,

1192
00:38:07,698 --> 00:38:09,737
- you have to pack gauze inside it. - It goes in all the way.

1193
00:38:09,738 --> 00:38:11,807
And if I exaggerate a little,

1194
00:38:11,808 --> 00:38:13,707
it goes all the way up to the eyes.

1195
00:38:13,708 --> 00:38:15,037
- It should go in. - It goes up a lot.

1196
00:38:15,038 --> 00:38:16,638
- Even Seok Ju... - Right.

1197
00:38:17,148 --> 00:38:20,177
When you score a goal, your adrenaline explodes...

1198
00:38:20,178 --> 00:38:22,048
- and you get excited. - Right.

1199
00:38:22,348 --> 00:38:24,388
- It kicks in even when you get hit. - Even then.

1200
00:38:24,848 --> 00:38:26,848
- It kicks in even then. - That's right.

1201
00:38:27,048 --> 00:38:28,188
So you get so fired up...

1202
00:38:28,758 --> 00:38:30,627
that even if your nose is broken,

1203
00:38:30,628 --> 00:38:33,557
you think, "I'll go out there and take him down with me."

1204
00:38:33,558 --> 00:38:35,757
You keep playing like that.

1205
00:38:35,758 --> 00:38:38,398
I think that's why Coach Hiddink...

1206
00:38:38,598 --> 00:38:41,198
substituted me out in the second half against Italy.

1207
00:38:42,438 --> 00:38:44,308
- Then... - I think I got angrier and angrier.

1208
00:38:44,368 --> 00:38:46,607
Did the mask exist before,

1209
00:38:46,608 --> 00:38:47,877
or did you wear it for the first time?

1210
00:38:47,878 --> 00:38:50,037
I think it was made in a hurry back then.

1211
00:38:50,038 --> 00:38:51,247
In the shape of the Taegeuk, right?

1212
00:38:51,248 --> 00:38:54,648
People flew over from Japan...

1213
00:38:55,148 --> 00:38:56,848
- to make it. - That's right. It didn't exist.

1214
00:38:56,918 --> 00:38:59,147
- That was... - Right.

1215
00:38:59,148 --> 00:39:01,858
- like 24 or 25 years ago. - Like 24 or 25 years ago.

1216
00:39:02,358 --> 00:39:04,987
- Masks these days are... - Son Heung Min's mask was cool.

1217
00:39:04,988 --> 00:39:06,157
He fractured his eye socket.

1218
00:39:06,158 --> 00:39:07,857
It's custom-made these days.

1219
00:39:07,858 --> 00:39:09,028
- To fit the bone. - Is it different?

1220
00:39:09,598 --> 00:39:11,167
Right. There's a big difference...

1221
00:39:11,168 --> 00:39:12,697
- between now and back then. - It would be a huge difference.

1222
00:39:12,698 --> 00:39:14,067
- Right. - It's made of carbon,

1223
00:39:14,068 --> 00:39:15,437
so it's really light.

1224
00:39:15,438 --> 00:39:16,597
It's way lighter.

1225
00:39:16,598 --> 00:39:19,108
- Even the field of vision... - It also fits perfectly.

1226
00:39:19,208 --> 00:39:21,477
Since it's made using a mould of your face.

1227
00:39:21,478 --> 00:39:24,578
The one I wore would absorb sweat.

1228
00:39:25,078 --> 00:39:26,507
The back was just a regular rubber band.

1229
00:39:26,508 --> 00:39:27,518
- Rubber band. - A black band.

1230
00:39:27,978 --> 00:39:30,418
Back then, even if I had a broken nose,

1231
00:39:30,648 --> 00:39:31,687
my legs were fine.

1232
00:39:31,688 --> 00:39:32,787
- That's right. - I could still run.

1233
00:39:32,788 --> 00:39:36,118
Back then, I was 33 years old.

1234
00:39:36,458 --> 00:39:38,928
So I thought that was going to be my last World Soccer Games.

1235
00:39:39,028 --> 00:39:40,028
(Tae Young's final World Soccer Games, where he shone the brightest)

1236
00:39:40,029 --> 00:39:42,528
- That's so cool. - What do you think about this?

1237
00:39:42,658 --> 00:39:45,397
- Tae Young wore number seven. - That's right.

1238
00:39:45,398 --> 00:39:47,597
That number was later inherited by Park Ji Sung...

1239
00:39:47,598 --> 00:39:49,367
- and Son Heung Min. - That's right.

1240
00:39:49,368 --> 00:39:50,398
What do you think about this?

1241
00:39:51,438 --> 00:39:52,567
I can't understand it.

1242
00:39:52,568 --> 00:39:54,677
(I can't understand it.)

1243
00:39:54,678 --> 00:39:56,377
You'd understand Son Heung Min, right?

1244
00:39:56,378 --> 00:39:58,107
- I also understand Park Ji Sung. - You understand Park Ji Sung.

1245
00:39:58,108 --> 00:39:59,307
- But... - I don't understand Kim Tae Young.

1246
00:39:59,308 --> 00:40:03,047
I'm curious. Defenders...

1247
00:40:03,048 --> 00:40:05,387
- don't usually wear number 7. - They normally wear number 4 or 3.

1248
00:40:05,388 --> 00:40:06,988
Why did Tae Young wear number seven?

1249
00:40:07,218 --> 00:40:09,718
Coach asked me what number I wanted.

1250
00:40:09,788 --> 00:40:11,088
I kept wearing number seven.

1251
00:40:11,488 --> 00:40:13,587
But in the 1998 World Soccer Games,

1252
00:40:13,588 --> 00:40:15,797
- I wore number 13. - Number 13.

1253
00:40:15,798 --> 00:40:19,368
Another player came in, so I gave him number seven.

1254
00:40:19,668 --> 00:40:21,438
After the 1998 World Soccer Games,

1255
00:40:21,638 --> 00:40:22,697
I wore number seven...

1256
00:40:22,698 --> 00:40:23,967
- until I retired. - I see.

1257
00:40:23,968 --> 00:40:25,767
- What number did you wear, Seok Ju? - Number 17.

1258
00:40:25,768 --> 00:40:27,308
I wore numbers 9 and 17.

1259
00:40:27,608 --> 00:40:28,907
- Why did you wear number 9? - Number 9?

1260
00:40:28,908 --> 00:40:31,177
I wore number nine when I first joined the national team.

1261
00:40:31,178 --> 00:40:32,707
- Number nine. - I was a center-forward.

1262
00:40:32,708 --> 00:40:34,948
What does number 17 mean?

1263
00:40:35,048 --> 00:40:36,417
It has no meaning.

1264
00:40:36,418 --> 00:40:38,647
You just took what was left?

1265
00:40:38,648 --> 00:40:40,147
That's what I wore at first,

1266
00:40:40,148 --> 00:40:41,918
and I just kept wearing it.

1267
00:40:42,818 --> 00:40:43,927
What about Young Kwang?

1268
00:40:43,928 --> 00:40:45,527
- Number 0? - I wore number 41...

1269
00:40:45,528 --> 00:40:47,088
at my professional soccer team.

1270
00:40:47,398 --> 00:40:48,928
- And I retired with that number. - You retired.

1271
00:40:49,158 --> 00:40:50,967
Goalkeepers used to wear number one.

1272
00:40:50,968 --> 00:40:51,998
- It was always number 1. - Number 1.

1273
00:40:52,168 --> 00:40:54,438
Number 21 was the 2nd goalkeeper,

1274
00:40:55,038 --> 00:40:57,867
number 31 was the 3rd, and so on. There were 4 goalkeepers.

1275
00:40:57,868 --> 00:40:59,468
I received the number of the fourth goalkeeper.

1276
00:40:59,938 --> 00:41:01,338
- It really hurt my pride. - Right.

1277
00:41:01,678 --> 00:41:03,177
I told myself I’d turn it into a starting player's number...

1278
00:41:03,178 --> 00:41:04,308
within a year,

1279
00:41:04,848 --> 00:41:06,277
and I achieved that goal.

1280
00:41:06,278 --> 00:41:08,478
I started with number 41 and kept it all the way until I retired.

1281
00:41:08,678 --> 00:41:10,417
I even played until I was 41 wearing number 41.

1282
00:41:10,418 --> 00:41:11,687
(He retired at 41 wearing number 41.)

1283
00:41:11,688 --> 00:41:12,818
- That was meaningful. - They...

1284
00:41:13,118 --> 00:41:15,058
begged him to leave the team,

1285
00:41:15,858 --> 00:41:17,018
but he didn't leave.

1286
00:41:17,088 --> 00:41:18,887
- But he was... - He didn't leave...

1287
00:41:18,888 --> 00:41:20,127
- until the end... - The contract...

1288
00:41:20,128 --> 00:41:22,297
- I stayed there for two more years. - "All right. You can now..."

1289
00:41:22,298 --> 00:41:25,127
He told them he'd stay even if they paid him less,

1290
00:41:25,128 --> 00:41:26,527
- so he stayed until the very end. - It was because of Byung Ji.

1291
00:41:26,528 --> 00:41:29,638
I tried to stay there to break his record.

1292
00:41:30,238 --> 00:41:32,067
I would have had to play for three more years.

1293
00:41:32,068 --> 00:41:34,078
So I said, "No, I'm done," and left.

1294
00:41:34,308 --> 00:41:36,237
Tae Young. Do you still have...

1295
00:41:36,238 --> 00:41:38,478
- the mask? - Yes, I have it framed.

1296
00:41:38,578 --> 00:41:39,777
It's there.

1297
00:41:39,778 --> 00:41:41,278
(The mask is carefully kept.)

1298
00:41:41,548 --> 00:41:43,447
That's really cool,

1299
00:41:43,448 --> 00:41:45,387
but when you compare it with the masks these days,

1300
00:41:45,388 --> 00:41:46,748
- It's different. - it's so...

1301
00:41:47,288 --> 00:41:50,558
It still would have given you some psychological comfort.

1302
00:41:50,658 --> 00:41:52,287
- Of course. - Just the fact that you wore it...

1303
00:41:52,288 --> 00:41:55,057
- would make you feel protected. - Yes. I felt protected.

1304
00:41:55,058 --> 00:41:56,928
What about Seok Ju and Young Kwang?

1305
00:41:57,258 --> 00:42:00,598
Do you have any treasured items from your playing days?

1306
00:42:00,738 --> 00:42:02,867
Actually, I like giving things.

1307
00:42:02,868 --> 00:42:04,367
I was on the national team for 11 years,

1308
00:42:04,368 --> 00:42:05,838
but I don’t have anything from the national team.

1309
00:42:06,268 --> 00:42:07,307
You gave them all out...

1310
00:42:07,308 --> 00:42:08,378
- to your friends. - Everything.

1311
00:42:08,538 --> 00:42:10,177
I gave them out to my friends and acquaintances.

1312
00:42:10,178 --> 00:42:11,448
They didn't believe me,

1313
00:42:11,608 --> 00:42:12,677
so I sent it to them...

1314
00:42:12,678 --> 00:42:13,748
- when they gave me their addresses. - They wouldn't believe you?

1315
00:42:14,078 --> 00:42:15,778
- I don't have a single thing. - Really?

1316
00:42:16,078 --> 00:42:17,078
- What about Young Kwang? - You should've kept the red card...

1317
00:42:17,079 --> 00:42:18,088
from the Mexico match.

1318
00:42:20,048 --> 00:42:21,388
You almost got hit just now.

1319
00:42:21,558 --> 00:42:23,058
- You almost got hit just now. - He should have kept it.

1320
00:42:23,388 --> 00:42:24,958
Let's take a one-minute break.

1321
00:42:25,488 --> 00:42:26,988
- No. - Not yet.

1322
00:42:27,128 --> 00:42:29,357
- We'll take a break later. - The red card?

1323
00:42:29,358 --> 00:42:31,227
Do you have any keepsakes, Young Kwang?

1324
00:42:31,228 --> 00:42:33,428
I got more attention during...

1325
00:42:33,998 --> 00:42:36,197
the International Sports Events than I did on the national team.

1326
00:42:36,198 --> 00:42:38,407
You don't feel pain anyway, so just keep the anesthetic.

1327
00:42:38,408 --> 00:42:39,907
(You don't feel pain anyway, so just keep the anesthetic.)

1328
00:42:39,908 --> 00:42:41,408
"Just keep the anesthetic."

1329
00:42:41,638 --> 00:42:43,278
You should speak kindly first.

1330
00:42:43,508 --> 00:42:44,847
That's so childish.

1331
00:42:44,848 --> 00:42:46,578
It's so childish, but it's funny.

1332
00:42:46,778 --> 00:42:49,278
- He's 16 years older than me. - "Just keep the anesthetic."

1333
00:42:49,548 --> 00:42:51,117
He's 16 years older than you.

1334
00:42:51,118 --> 00:42:52,647
- He's childish. - "Just keep the anesthetic."

1335
00:42:52,648 --> 00:42:53,987
We're all friends here.

1336
00:42:53,988 --> 00:42:56,017
- Yes. We're all friends here. - He's old, just like an uncle.

1337
00:42:56,018 --> 00:42:58,327
During the final qualifying matches in the International Sports Events,

1338
00:42:58,328 --> 00:43:00,258
I kept a clean sheet in all six matches.

1339
00:43:00,588 --> 00:43:02,697
- That's right. - That's never happened before.

1340
00:43:02,698 --> 00:43:04,667
I went nearly 1,000 minutes without conceding a goal,

1341
00:43:04,668 --> 00:43:06,998
setting an unofficial world record. The gloves I used then.

1342
00:43:07,568 --> 00:43:09,937
- You have those gloves, right? - I still have them.

1343
00:43:09,938 --> 00:43:12,667
(He still has the gloves that were part of the history.)

1344
00:43:12,668 --> 00:43:14,637
- I have it at home. - As you all know, Young Kwang...

1345
00:43:14,638 --> 00:43:16,377
- is a really amazing player. - He is.

1346
00:43:16,378 --> 00:43:18,147
But he wrote "unlucky player."

1347
00:43:18,148 --> 00:43:19,577
- You said it when you came in. - Right.

1348
00:43:19,578 --> 00:43:21,347
- You didn't concede a single goal. - A clean sheet.

1349
00:43:21,348 --> 00:43:22,377
A clean sheet.

1350
00:43:22,378 --> 00:43:23,417
I kept a clean sheet...

1351
00:43:23,418 --> 00:43:24,647
- because I didn't play. - Right.

1352
00:43:24,648 --> 00:43:26,448
You can't concede a goal if you don't even get to play.

1353
00:43:27,888 --> 00:43:28,988
I just sat on the bench.

1354
00:43:29,118 --> 00:43:31,557
- He just sat on the bench. - That's right.

1355
00:43:31,558 --> 00:43:34,157
- He's there now. - He mentioned the Garrincha Club.

1356
00:43:34,158 --> 00:43:35,428
Honestly, I envied him.

1357
00:43:36,458 --> 00:43:38,367
That's an absurd thing to be jealous of. The Garrincha Club?

1358
00:43:38,368 --> 00:43:41,297
I wanted to play at least one match, even if I’d get sent off.

1359
00:43:41,298 --> 00:43:42,298
That's right.

1360
00:43:42,299 --> 00:43:44,568
Even if it goes down in the record like that.

1361
00:43:44,868 --> 00:43:47,778
You would have played in the qualifiers, right?

1362
00:43:47,878 --> 00:43:49,308
- I didn't. - You didn't.

1363
00:43:49,408 --> 00:43:51,707
The competition for the goalkeeper spot...

1364
00:43:51,708 --> 00:43:53,147
- It was overwhelming. - back then was…

1365
00:43:53,148 --> 00:43:55,217
- It was so much... - There were Lee Woon Jae,

1366
00:43:55,218 --> 00:43:56,778
- Jung Sung Ryong... - that Jung Hwan...

1367
00:43:57,418 --> 00:44:00,248
Jung Hwan and Kim Nam Il...

1368
00:44:00,888 --> 00:44:03,158
didn't even remember they went with him.

1369
00:44:04,158 --> 00:44:05,228
(I'm sorry, but I also...)

1370
00:44:05,358 --> 00:44:07,228
(don't think I went to the World Soccer Games with you.)

1371
00:44:07,388 --> 00:44:09,998
(You went to the World Soccer Games with me twice?)

1372
00:44:10,198 --> 00:44:14,067
(Young Kwang was always there,)

1373
00:44:14,068 --> 00:44:16,468
(one step behind him.)

1374
00:44:16,798 --> 00:44:18,638
I guess that was why I couldn't play in the World Soccer Games.

1375
00:44:18,968 --> 00:44:20,268
(Did you go to the World Soccer Games?)

1376
00:44:21,408 --> 00:44:23,537
This is sad.

1377
00:44:23,538 --> 00:44:24,777
No one remembers him.

1378
00:44:24,778 --> 00:44:26,578
Young Kwang, couldn't you say,

1379
00:44:26,878 --> 00:44:29,478
"I want to play, Coach?"

1380
00:44:29,878 --> 00:44:30,988
Couldn't you say something like that?

1381
00:44:31,418 --> 00:44:32,688
You get kicked out if you say things like that.

1382
00:44:33,418 --> 00:44:34,418
- You get kicked out... - I wasn't in a position...

1383
00:44:34,419 --> 00:44:36,217
- if you say things like that? - to say something like that.

1384
00:44:36,218 --> 00:44:38,157
You must have been a little resentful inside.

1385
00:44:38,158 --> 00:44:41,697
What would have to happen for him to get a chance to play?

1386
00:44:41,698 --> 00:44:42,727
- A foreign coach? - The goalkeeper...

1387
00:44:42,728 --> 00:44:43,728
would have to get injured.

1388
00:44:43,729 --> 00:44:45,568
- In that situation? - For you to play.

1389
00:44:45,668 --> 00:44:47,128
The two goalkeepers would have to get injured.

1390
00:44:47,428 --> 00:44:49,837
I was the second goalkeeper in 2006. I was the second.

1391
00:44:49,838 --> 00:44:51,968
- The second. - When Woon Jae was playing,

1392
00:44:53,538 --> 00:44:55,038
I'd think, "Maybe he’ll break his ankle."

1393
00:44:55,578 --> 00:44:57,178
"Maybe he'll break his ankle."

1394
00:44:57,808 --> 00:44:59,107
- It can happen since you're human. - That's a dangerous...

1395
00:44:59,108 --> 00:45:00,247
- thought. - I'm only human.

1396
00:45:00,248 --> 00:45:03,117
- Right. - But anyone would think that...

1397
00:45:03,118 --> 00:45:04,747
- Of course. - in that situation.

1398
00:45:04,748 --> 00:45:06,187
- I was cheering, but... - You hope the person...

1399
00:45:06,188 --> 00:45:07,588
- isn't in good form. - That's right.

1400
00:45:07,858 --> 00:45:08,858
Because that way, I can get a chance to play.

1401
00:45:09,058 --> 00:45:10,117
Goalkeepers don't get subbed off easily,

1402
00:45:10,118 --> 00:45:11,187
even when they’re not in good form.

1403
00:45:11,188 --> 00:45:13,288
- That's right. - They'd have to break something...

1404
00:45:14,658 --> 00:45:16,458
- Or get carried off. - or get carried off.

1405
00:45:17,158 --> 00:45:19,127
- Then... - It'd be hard to get a chance.

1406
00:45:19,128 --> 00:45:20,668
- Right. - Changing the goalkeeper...

1407
00:45:21,568 --> 00:45:24,468
- can disrupt the whole system. - Right.

1408
00:45:24,608 --> 00:45:26,237
- But... - So they wouldn't change them.

1409
00:45:26,238 --> 00:45:27,877
If you're desperate like that...

1410
00:45:27,878 --> 00:45:29,577
Sometimes,

1411
00:45:29,578 --> 00:45:30,907
goalkeepers might...

1412
00:45:30,908 --> 00:45:32,247
- concede even a single goal. - That's right.

1413
00:45:32,248 --> 00:45:34,247
When he concedes a goal, you could go to the coach.

1414
00:45:34,248 --> 00:45:36,477
Appealing like... "Coach."

1415
00:45:36,478 --> 00:45:37,547
You could tell him you could play as well.

1416
00:45:37,548 --> 00:45:39,047
"Please, Coach."

1417
00:45:39,048 --> 00:45:40,847
- The moment I do that, - You'll get shut out.

1418
00:45:40,848 --> 00:45:42,217
I might be pushed down to a standby spot.

1419
00:45:42,218 --> 00:45:43,988
- A standby spot. - They send you back to Korea...

1420
00:45:44,158 --> 00:45:45,858
- for bringing down the mood. - Really?

1421
00:45:46,588 --> 00:45:48,197
- That's right. - I'm sorry, but that...

1422
00:45:48,198 --> 00:45:50,297
- only happens in comic books. - That's right.

1423
00:45:50,298 --> 00:45:51,967
In sports comics, the player says, "I'm sorry,"

1424
00:45:51,968 --> 00:45:53,598
"but it's my mother's birthday today."

1425
00:45:53,668 --> 00:45:57,367
"I want to dedicate this goal to my mother in paradise."

1426
00:45:57,368 --> 00:45:59,668
Then the coach says, "Okay. You may play."

1427
00:45:59,968 --> 00:46:02,377
He cries, "Mother!" and scores a goal.

1428
00:46:02,378 --> 00:46:03,838
He then cries out.

1429
00:46:04,038 --> 00:46:05,748
"Did you see that, Mother?"

1430
00:46:06,078 --> 00:46:08,518
His mother says, "Yes, my son." That happens in comic books.

1431
00:46:08,778 --> 00:46:10,818
"That's my son!"

1432
00:46:11,018 --> 00:46:13,087
"It's snowing, Mother."

1433
00:46:13,088 --> 00:46:15,788
- That happens in comic books. - But...

1434
00:46:15,888 --> 00:46:17,928
- He's saying that doesn't happen. - That happens in comic books.

1435
00:46:18,528 --> 00:46:22,758
Young Kwang may have been unlucky on the national team,

1436
00:46:22,998 --> 00:46:24,298
but on the K League,

1437
00:46:25,128 --> 00:46:28,697
- he played 605 games, - He is a legendary player.

1438
00:46:28,698 --> 00:46:30,337
- the second-most in history. - Right.

1439
00:46:30,338 --> 00:46:31,537
In the history of Korea.

1440
00:46:31,538 --> 00:46:32,767
- That's an amazing record. - Six hundred five games.

1441
00:46:32,768 --> 00:46:34,407
How many games do players mostly play?

1442
00:46:34,408 --> 00:46:35,837
I played 250 games...

1443
00:46:35,838 --> 00:46:36,877
- in the K League... - He played in the national team.

1444
00:46:36,878 --> 00:46:38,677
- and 100 in the national team. - He still can't beat me.

1445
00:46:38,678 --> 00:46:39,777
- Two hundred fifty. - I also played...

1446
00:46:39,778 --> 00:46:41,718
250 games in the K League and 100 games in the J League.

1447
00:46:42,378 --> 00:46:43,517
Then 94 games in the national team.

1448
00:46:43,518 --> 00:46:44,587
You played in the J League.

1449
00:46:44,588 --> 00:46:46,448
- Right. - One hundred games in the J League.

1450
00:46:46,818 --> 00:46:48,187
I played 605 games in the K League...

1451
00:46:48,188 --> 00:46:49,588
and 18 games in the national team.

1452
00:46:49,688 --> 00:46:50,788
- Goodness. - Only 18 games?

1453
00:46:51,058 --> 00:46:53,927
- That's nice. - That's a fine number of games.

1454
00:46:53,928 --> 00:46:56,298
He wasn't just second in appearances. Clean sheet?

1455
00:46:56,628 --> 00:46:59,228
- He also had 175 clean sheets. - No goals conceded.

1456
00:46:59,728 --> 00:47:01,737
- The 2nd. - Why were you always in 2nd place?

1457
00:47:01,738 --> 00:47:02,838
- Who was the first? - Right.

1458
00:47:03,338 --> 00:47:05,168
That was Byung Ji, who played until he was 46.

1459
00:47:05,708 --> 00:47:07,037
Byung Ji, who played until he was 46.

1460
00:47:07,038 --> 00:47:08,978
Can you even play soccer until you're 46?

1461
00:47:10,608 --> 00:47:12,147
Kim Byung Ji who was in Ulsan Hyundai.

1462
00:47:12,148 --> 00:47:14,578
- I'm really... - This is serious.

1463
00:47:14,678 --> 00:47:15,777
- His long hair at the back. - He's good.

1464
00:47:15,778 --> 00:47:17,347
- That's right. - You know...

1465
00:47:17,348 --> 00:47:19,287
- He did it until 46? - I really hate Seok Ju here.

1466
00:47:19,288 --> 00:47:21,687
- Why? - If it hadn't been for Seok Ju,

1467
00:47:21,688 --> 00:47:23,418
I would have been number one.

1468
00:47:24,217 --> 00:47:25,226
How come?

1469
00:47:25,227 --> 00:47:27,257
When Seok Ju was the coach of the team Byung Ji was in...

1470
00:47:27,557 --> 00:47:29,056
- He really... - I brought him with me.

1471
00:47:29,057 --> 00:47:30,557
liked Byung Ji a lot.

1472
00:47:31,197 --> 00:47:32,766
He kept sending him in matches,

1473
00:47:32,767 --> 00:47:34,296
so his number of appearances kept increasing.

1474
00:47:34,297 --> 00:47:35,366
From which team?

1475
00:47:35,367 --> 00:47:37,196
- From Jeonnam. - When I was the coach of Jeonnam,

1476
00:47:37,197 --> 00:47:39,266
Byung Ji came to me from Gyeongnam FC.

1477
00:47:39,267 --> 00:47:40,336
I see.

1478
00:47:40,337 --> 00:47:42,276
So he played for another three years.

1479
00:47:42,277 --> 00:47:43,336
- Until he turned 46? - If I'd played for 3 more years,

1480
00:47:43,337 --> 00:47:44,407
I would've broken the record.

1481
00:47:45,377 --> 00:47:46,647
Because he respected the coach?

1482
00:47:47,377 --> 00:47:48,617
Because he respected me.

1483
00:47:49,347 --> 00:47:51,417
- I see. - I'm respected like that.

1484
00:47:52,617 --> 00:47:55,216
- Hang on. Young Kwang... - Why do you think...

1485
00:47:55,217 --> 00:47:58,187
the junior players respect you?

1486
